    <poem name="fwd" id="fwd-100" seq="100" date="2015-08-23" time="23:11" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>Two parts</line>
        <line>One feeling inside</line>
        <line>One doing outside</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>They are not one</line>
        <line>Or</line>
        <line>They were</line>
        <line>But started to divert</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>The doing one is newer</line>
        <line>The feeling one is behind</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>There is a separation I can’t control yet</line>
        <line>If that is appropriate even</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Sometimes one overrides the other</line>
        <line>Feeling over doing</line>
        <line>Doing over feeling</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Before it was mostly feeling over doing</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="got it" id="got-it-101" seq="101" date="2015-08-23" time="22:44" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>My own wisdom</line>
        <line>Rules</line>
        <line>The ether</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Speech is sound waves</line>
        <line>Lots of waves</line>
        <line>Lots of noise</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Good to vent</line>
        <line>Good to get 2nd opinions</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I think in a clear moment of candid weakness that all that is wrong</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Thus my own wisdom is formed slowly</line>
        <line>And this little gem is no big stepping stone</line>
        <line>But it shines in the sunlight</line>
        <line>On its own</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="daemon core" id="daemon-core-102" seq="102" date="2015-08-25" time="11:11" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>blue light flash</line>
        <line>critical mass</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>black oil fills your eyes</line>
        <line>soaks your head</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>flesh swells</line>
        <line>morphine no cure</line>
        <line>visiting hours cancelled</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>not much longer now</line>
        <line>irreversible execution</line>
        <line>no stay</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>jinxed metallic</line>
        <line>daemon core</line>
        <line>reaps twice</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>human curiosity and will for destruction</line>
        <line>termination is the single point</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>exodus and fail</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="passive aggressive person" id="passive-aggressive-person-103" seq="103" date="2015-08-26" time="20:39" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>this PAP trying to bitch step on my nerves</line>
        <line>that never works</line>
        <line>it will back fire up your face</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I am not that easy to manipulate, unless in love</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>endless hours talking</line>
        <line>endless hours whining, I realize</line>
        <line>endless hours bla bla land</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>doing’ the rite th’ng?</line>
        <line>make me feel sorry?</line>
        <line>what did that help - PAP!</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line caesura="1">trying to make me feel/do something I won’t?</line>
        <line>trying to make me feel bad, for nothing?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>yeah,</line>
        <line>life is misery</line>
        <line>life is pain</line>
        <line>so unfair</line>
        <line>oh yeah!</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>do it or don’t, but no asking me helps!</line>
        <line>fuck off!</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="no damn ET types" id="no-damn-et-types-104" seq="104" date="2015-08-26" time="20:52" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>endless plains of sand</line>
        <line>walking slowly</line>
        <line>seeing the mountains distant</line>
        <line>not many clouds</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>some ghost people</line>
        <line>around, quiet</line>
        <line>not alone,</line>
        <line>not lonely</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>all about point of view</line>
        <line>all about line of sight</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the imposition</line>
        <line>of frozen cathedrals</line>
        <line>gothic in shape</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>spiders running before you</line>
        <line>abstract plains with planes intersecting the air mass above</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>old beer can rattling,</line>
        <line>Pabst blue ribbon - fuck that Heineken shit (Frank says)!</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>old rusty Ford</line>
        <line>fire and forget</line>
        <line>but starts this evening</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>starry and moon glued to my head</line>
        <line>steering avoiding traps</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>vaguely following traces by ancient wheels</line>
        <line>passed away</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>neverland of lostness</line>
        <line>out here</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>graceland of Kingness</line>
        <line>out there</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I see them</line>
        <line>by their vessel</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>not supposed to</line>
        <line>be like this</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>scared hellish</line>
        <line>these ain’t no damn ET types</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I guess my end is near</line>
        <line>and all traces ending here</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>if you find my stuff</line>
        <line>can you please post a note on FB?</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="today" id="today-105" seq="105" date="2015-08-28" time="16:43" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>relaxed day, flowing around with no contours</line>
        <line>good messages all around</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>no pain or suffering to report, Captain!</line>
        <line>no sight of the enemy</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the thin red line is not visible</line>
        <line>afternoon clouds gather behind the Sandias</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>imminent breakthrough?</line>
        <line>still ok to sip on bad Sangrias?</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="slice" id="slice-106" seq="106" date="2015-08-30" time="21:14" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>yellow water blank beneath</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>when we play, let’s pretend</line>
        <line>all this have been pretend, I see now</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>hearing the tones</line>
        <line>seeing the memories play out</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>even in a situation</line>
        <line>mix of all things creates</line>
        <line>untruth from ‘my’ perspective</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>somewhere else very close there is a truth slice</line>
        <line>cannot get hold of it</line>
        <line>without releasing the whole mass of ‘me’</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>oh, so blown up</line>
        <line>swollen and exaggerated</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>ourselves trying to get ahead</line>
        <line>trying to say something else</line>
        <line>believing it is our turn now</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>jumping into the yellow pool tonight</line>
        <line>the yellow river</line>
        <line>the yellow blankness</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>well under</line>
        <line>formations of bubbles</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>people I remember</line>
        <line>and dogs</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>monologues</line>
        <line>I recall</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>advice</line>
        <line>I recite</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>wisdom</line>
        <line>I thought</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>containment</line>
        <line>I sought</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>escape</line>
        <line>I tried but no way</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>need air, cracking the surface</line>
        <line>all searches exhausted</line>
        <line>only the slice</line>
        <line>completely immersed</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>any statement kills</line>
        <line>any proposal kills</line>
        <line>any reference kills</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I just thought I needed to do that</line>
        <line>but I am wrong</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>enter the slice…</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>statements are based on fear, in search of certainty</line>
        <line>proposal are based on power, in search of control</line>
        <line>references are based on fuzziness, in search of acknowledgement</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>can we throw the anchor</line>
        <line>can we enter the slice</line>
        <line>where there is an existence pure and fresh</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I keep repeating jumping in the yellow</line>
        <line>getting exhausted</line>
        <line>being trapped in all of this</line>
        <line>being trapped in my web of inventions</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>playfullness...</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>these dogs rolling in the grass</line>
        <line>exhausted driving in the desert</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>packing my bags</line>
        <line>Evian bottle getting too warm</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>swamp cooler humming</line>
        <line>White car yellow lights rolling by</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>dust on the floor, for another day</line>
        <line>spider web left</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>broken glass bulb</line>
        <line>window locked with wooden pin</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>water puddle reflecting</line>
        <line>whirl of sand circling</line>
        <line>shadow hiding a coin forgotten</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>little girl with pony tail tying her shoes</line>
        <line>eraser fell out of her backpack</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>light switching to red</line>
        <line>the car tried to make it, next time?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>bus just left, no people waiting</line>
        <line>someone is going to get these dogs back home</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="truth slices" id="truth-slices-107" seq="107" date="2015-08-31" time="22:02" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>these dogs rolling in the grass</line>
        <line>exhausted driving in the desert</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>packing my bags</line>
        <line>Evian bottle getting warm</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>swamp cooler humming</line>
        <line>white car yellow lights rolling by</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>dust on the floor, for another day</line>
        <line>spider web left</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>broken glass bulb</line>
        <line>window locked with wooden pin</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>water puddle reflecting</line>
        <line>whirl of sand circling</line>
        <line>shadow hiding a coin forgotten</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>little girl with pony tail tying her shoes</line>
        <line>eraser fell out of her backpack</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>light switching to red</line>
        <line>the car tried to make it, next time?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>bus just left, no people waiting</line>
        <line>someone is going to get these dogs back home</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>little girl crying soo much not finding her eraser</line>
        <line>bubblegum scent</line>
        <line>first day of school and all</line>
        <line>but she found a coin in a puddle</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>her parents not understanding a new eraser tomorrow is not the same thing</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>a white car with yellow lights a la France is a rare occurrence</line>
        <line>reflected in the puddles</line>
        <line>don't splash!</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Evian is the smoothest</line>
        <line>warm it is acceptable still, but just</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>trying to get cooler odor out of the cooler</line>
        <line>impossible, like coffee smell in a thermos</line>
        <line>they say toothpaste helps</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>these humming sounds around us</line>
        <line>all the un-noticeables</line>
        <line>spider webs abandoned</line>
        <line>beer bottle broken</line>
        <line>each its own slice</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>dear blanket not used this time</line>
        <line>a bit nostalgic</line>
        <line>so much it remembers</line>
        <line>few grains of sand</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>two thin dogs chasing in the empty park</line>
        <line>people at the bus stop watching and yawning</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="light hearted" id="light-hearted-109" seq="109" date="2015-09-03" time="21:47" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>Light hearted</line>
        <line>No worries</line>
        <line>Thoughts come</line>
        <line>Won't stay too long</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Ah!</line>
        <line>No effort</line>
        <line>No force</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>This happens</line>
        <line>Today</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Maybe not tomorrow</line>
        <line>Or the day after</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>But it doesn't matter</line>
        <line>Because now I know</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>A step further into some direction without any name</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="night wishes" id="night-wishes-110" seq="110" date="2015-09-03" time="23:21" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>All us sentients and celestials</line>
        <line>Need to sleep at times</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>The Earth clock sometimes have too few dial markers</line>
        <line>for everything to be wrapped up</line>
        <line>like a burrito so neat</line>
        <line>nothing to leak, no dripping of sauce</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>The struggle between the Day Mind and the Night Mind, I call out</line>
        <line>They need very soon to meet and embrace each other…</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Else big yawns hunt me all day</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Trying to outrun these ghosts in a desolate alley with the old weird trees laughing at me!</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="cloudy" id="cloudy-111" seq="111" date="2015-09-05" time="08:30" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>Weather report Albuquerque:</line>
        <line>It is an awful day</line>
        <line>No sun just gray</line>
        <line>But is is o-kay :-)</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="cloudy II" id="cloudy-ii-112" seq="112" date="2015-09-05" time="17:57" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>Weather update Albuquerque:</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>It is an awful refrain</line>
        <line>No sun just rain</line>
        <line>This starting to eat my brain</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Unless the sunburnt zombies get here first…</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="im" id="im-113" seq="113" date="2015-09-05" time="21:51" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>IM sending messages from Heaven</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>instructing the IMortal Coil</line>
        <line>preparations occur swiftly</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>IM sending message from Hell</line>
        <line>preparing the Landing Fields</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>IMminent approach, ETA T-1, counting</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>IMediate response requested.</line>
        <line>No further delay is accepted.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Blurred Lights IMgnited</line>
        <line>White lights enabled</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>As the Vessel IMaterialises</line>
        <line>Ground contact acknowledged</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>And there it is in its splendid remarkable eerie beauty and blackness</line>
        <line>against backdrop of starry sky, moon is dIM</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>returning back to Base after 1000 of years being lost in</line>
        <line>IMmerse sky refuge</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>IM over and IM out</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="cracy bucy" id="cracy-bucy-114" seq="114" date="2015-09-07" time="23:27" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>been a cracy bucy weecend</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>driving writing loving drawing talking taking pictures meditating</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>being rained at, being sunshined at</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>been not sleeping</line>
        <line>	not eating</line>
        <line>	not weeping</line>
        <line>	not moonshined at</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="what a day!" id="what-a-day-115" seq="115" date="2015-09-08" time="16:45" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>and the world goes on</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Alice IWL escaped through the great emergency exit door,</line>
        <line>no one SANE to discuss geopolitical necessities with</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>as God and Dog are both dead at this point in time</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>as Tristan T in my bathroom is having a laugh on his own</line>
        <line>reading blogs from 1916</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>some important event at my company</line>
        <line>too abstract to absorb with Brawny</line>
        <line>Scotch Brite doesn’t Bite either</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>toothless pastries</line>
        <line>fell out of pocket</line>
        <line>can’t reach them behind crumbled dust clouds beyond my coach</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Alice Alive,</line>
        <line>came back for cell phone and car keys</line>
        <line>but she doesn’t have a car?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>trying to put my mind together following the IQ-EA manual</line>
        <line>missing some pieces</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>so I gave my partial mind to the Inter zone</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>and the world goes on</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="not working yet" id="not-working-yet-116" seq="116" date="2015-09-10" time="11:30" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>it got blue this week</line>
        <line>blue as in dark blue</line>
        <line>but not black</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>never almost black or black</line>
        <line>but darker blue</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>flavors loose their immediate sting</line>
        <line>a bit numb</line>
        <line>numb Cayenne</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>oddly enough</line>
        <line>writing makes it a bit lighter blue</line>
        <line>maybe turquoise?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>writing is wired deeper into the soul</line>
        <line>things we have to do for the Time-Being are not especially wired to anything</line>
        <line role="turn">- they are wirelessly attached with a weak signal and lots of noise</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>washing my skin with Numb Cayenne to</line>
        <line>get hold of that spark moving from Dark Blue to Red</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="went about and around" id="went-about-and-around-117" seq="117" date="2015-09-12" time="21:06" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>This beautiful state (NM), this beautiful land…</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>when  you leave Main Street</line>
        <line>for a blitz into the terrestrial empty fields</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>See Socorro -</line>
        <line>Dust between your teeth and behind closed Eyes</line>
        <line>Trying to decrypt the sun polished texts on faded signs</line>
        <line>‘Best Steak in the USA’ - doubt it, highly</line>
        <line>Though, being vegetarian I have no valid point of view</line>
        <line>Demolished buildings, fenced windows, despair and lostness</line>
        <line>But, suddenly arises from the Dust, a vivid and lively Plaza, sign of life, sign of hope?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Kelly’s Mine -</line>
        <line>Big Ol’ Rusty Theing</line>
        <line>Bullet holes</line>
        <line>Broken beer bottles</line>
        <line>Old remains of greater times</line>
        <line>When silver and zinc brought up in to the light from ominous deep hidden maze of body breaking tunnels dark</line>
        <line>Thousands of people living in piles of rock and debris, making a rough living, what a place for kids was that?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Pie Town -</line>
        <line>Except this day - passed in three seconds</line>
        <line>This day only -</line>
        <line>Navajo Frybread - head implodes when the harmless looking meal unleashes hurricane of red chile</line>
        <line>All these pies trying to git’ ya’…</line>
        <line>Gun carrying cowboys, horses</line>
        <line>Dogs, people, food, sun and cool breeze, a different feel here</line>
        <line>This day</line>
        <line>Only</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>El Malpais -</line>
        <line>The Badlands</line>
        <line>The exceptional stark beauty of uncovered ancient black black black lava mountains, ridges, rivers</line>
        <line>Sparsely covered by green trying to survive in this extreme spot</line>
        <line>Interwoven sandstone yellows and reds, arches of soft stone exploded by ice distant millions of years ago</line>
        <line>The silence and space mind wrecking here, a physical impact</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>There is a broken beauty about and around this state: land of Entrapment, land of Enchantment, land of Enhancement!</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="mind shower" id="mind-shower-118" seq="118" date="2015-09-14" time="19:28" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>Mind numbing day</line>
        <line>Tired and not ok</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>So I went to the Zendo</line>
        <line>Just sitting</line>
        <line>Just walking</line>
        <line>Just breathing</line>
        <line>Just not interfering with other things like thoughts, feelings, Buddhas, poetry, dogs, cats, stars, spiders</line>
        <line>Let em’ rest in their space</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Mind Shower -</line>
        <line>fresh and pure and mint conditioned</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="mind fuck" id="mind-fuck-119" seq="119" date="2015-09-16" time="15:46" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>Experiments..</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Mind fucks me this year</line>
        <line>I am going to fight it with the Unmind</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Friend misbehaves</line>
        <line>Going to snare him with the Unmind</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Boredom kills me</line>
        <line>Going to strangle it with the Unmind</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Planning and goals</line>
        <line>Going to put gasoline and ignite with the Unmind</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Vampire energy zapping Basterds!</line>
        <line>Going to spear them with the Unmind</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Unmind is not, and it is not graspable, but still not nothing.</line>
        <line>Not faith, not hope, not destiny, not anarchy, not nihilism, not luck.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Can't fight the mind with the mind, as a sword cannot cut itself in two. More subtle and radical means are needed here.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>L'Expérience continue...</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="mind revolt" id="mind-revolt-120" seq="120" date="2015-09-20" time="11:08" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>This awakened sense of freedom</line>
        <line>Mind boggling recent event</line>
        <line>Left me stranded on another shore</line>
        <line>Slightly elevated mood without understanding it clearly</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>No people involved</line>
        <line>Just this elevation without needing anything or anyone</line>
        <line>Without thinking needing anything or anyone</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>A clarity showing through</line>
        <line>A purity</line>
        <line>Nothing is needed</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Slowly burning fuse</line>
        <line>Reaching strands of attachments</line>
        <line>They go one by one</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Struggles ease as the Per-ma-frost is stubbornly giving up</line>
        <line>Why did I lock myself down so long?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Infinite light stretching its beam from infinite time, ETA TBD</line>
        <line>Absolute freedom in becoming?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>(I find myself taking breaths of relief without knowing why. It is peculiar and joyful. Really the sense of passing a gate I cannot see (so gate less).)</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="hard mind unboiled" id="hard-mind-unboiled-121" seq="121" date="2015-09-20" time="17:53" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>Seeking in all drawers, but can’t find it</line>
        <line>The external trigger</line>
        <line>The quick fix by habit</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Hearing nice sounding words</line>
        <line>Reading nice looking words</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>But, not really finding anything there</line>
        <line>Empty drawers…</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Old garbage and lint lying around</line>
        <line>Old truths repeated</line>
        <line>Old advice rehearsed</line>
        <line>Old men too old for the country</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>The search encircles itself</line>
        <line>Failed searches weigh less now</line>
        <line>The scent is not there to pick up, poor K-9s</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>So fundamentally it is all wrong</line>
        <line>Not just a little wrong</line>
        <line>Brutally wrong</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Have to rebuild and reconstruct all I know and knew</line>
        <line>Quite some work to do here</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Looking forward to the next moment</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="line" id="line-122" seq="122" date="2015-09-21" time="22:50" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>Sweep me away!</line>
        <line>Now I have reached full stop</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Of all came nothing, or almost</line>
        <line>As I suspected</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Betting on all horses and wrong horses</line>
        <line>Filling mind with emotions, no substance</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Listening as a good boy</line>
        <line>People do feel very hollow and distant</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>What is clarity?</line>
        <line>Is it found under the sun lying on the sand forever?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>—</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Been an adventure</line>
        <line>Now lost in the desert</line>
        <line>Sand blowing in my face</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>All the Mirages laughing at me</line>
        <line>Knew they were</line>
        <line>Hope they were not</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Silly me!</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>—</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Sweep me away!</line>
        <line>The elevator stuck between floors</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Something became of it all</line>
        <line>Not as I imagined</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Horses ran on the wrong track, the wrong day</line>
        <line>They didn’t know better, and neither did I</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>—</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>So the line is drawn and the sand storm is getting close now.</line>
        <line>Sweep me away dear friend!</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="blue flowers" id="blue-flowers-123" seq="123" date="2015-09-21" time="23:19" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>My breath is what is left</line>
        <line>All the images painted inside</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>But like etch-a-sketch</line>
        <line>Shake it all gone</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>A test tube</line>
        <line>A vacuum tube</line>
        <line>Mingle</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>A clean slate of enhanced evolution</line>
        <line>Elevated emotion</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>A green field with no cows</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>All look slightly different</line>
        <line>More distant</line>
        <line>more vivid</line>
        <line>and fresh</line>
        <line>after invisible rain bubbles</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>The nerve is electrified</line>
        <line>The heart still going</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>The breath not leaving my side</line>
        <line>blue flowers talking to me from behind closed doors</line>
        <line>of rooms inside rooms inside rooms</line>
        <line>Only when it is really quiet</line>
        <line>I can hear them through the pulse in my body</line>
        <line>Blood beat</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>It is all simple and clean now</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="colors 12" id="colors-12-124" seq="124" date="2015-09-21" time="23:40" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>All these vivid colors</line>
        <line>I see</line>
        <line>But not there</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Very strange</line>
        <line>Beyond rational</line>
        <line>Does anything exist?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>A bubbly laughter</line>
        <line>Can't hear</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Having 12 senses</line>
        <line>Concurrently served</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Vivid vivid</line>
        <line>Only sensing</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Such an exceptional freedom</line>
        <line>Only sensing</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>All talk and well intentions all my life</line>
        <line>All been zeroed out</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Point being to falsify</line>
        <line>Truth</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="step on it" id="step-on-it-125" seq="125" date="2015-09-22" time="00:01" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>For ward!</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I will beg for</line>
        <line>Give</line>
        <line>Ness</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Monster in a lake</line>
        <line>Chasing me down</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Wet sheets waking up</line>
        <line>Never remember dreams</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>But I sea monsters</line>
        <line>Behind corners</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Relentlessly they wait</line>
        <line>To remind me of dreams not recalled</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Under water documents etched on glass shards semi floating</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Hard to read hard to tell don't ask</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I am lossless at this point</line>
        <line>Nothing remembered nothing forgotten</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="estranged" id="estranged-126" seq="126" date="2015-09-22" time="15:34" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>Red haired dogs running up and down the streets</line>
        <line>The stupidity of everyday vegetation growing away</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Lego pieces we call humans trying to click</line>
        <line>These sticky humanoid shapes</line>
        <line>Hunting me down</line>
        <line>Through the ice cores</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Hide and seek</line>
        <line>In abandoned radar stations</line>
        <line>The dogs are after you</line>
        <line>The humans are after you</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>A crime not understood</line>
        <line>A revenge misunderstood</line>
        <line>Hiding behind metal doors</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Old control room with monitors green</line>
        <line>Burnt in pattern</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Throwing salt through closed windows is not a good idea</line>
        <line>Witches laugh at you</line>
        <line>Black cats thoughtfully crossing roads</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>—</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Running trapped under black ice</line>
        <line>Cracks above my head start to crackle and spring</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Escape!</line>
        <line>Before dogs and Lego soldiers pin me down with drones and well intended orders</line>
        <line>The stupidity of everyday intelligence eating away</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="new air" id="new-air-127" seq="127" date="2015-09-23" time="23:28" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>Fall air</line>
        <line>Getting colder</line>
        <line>Darkness seasons howling</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Opportunity to embrace the negative</line>
        <line>Go straight into it as heroes in horror movies</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Appreciate resistance</line>
        <line>Seek the challenge</line>
        <line>Comfort you will have in your coffin</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="traffic" id="traffic-128" seq="128" date="2015-09-25" time="21:33" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>It comes over me suddenly</line>
        <line>In a fresh way</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>It clears up</line>
        <line>The mud put to rest</line>
        <line>	the pond is quiet, frogs sleep</line>
        <line>The sky is so uncommonly deep</line>
        <line>The moon super crisp</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>The echoes are full of life</line>
        <line>The shadows emit their secrets</line>
        <line>In HD</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Can feel how absurd and sticky words can be</line>
        <line caesura="3">All the consumption/production/mangling/arguing</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Have to do it, though, still…</line>
        <line>But, losing value, losing touch</line>
        <line>This ain’t real -</line>
        <line>	badly made Gucci handbag replicas</line>
        <line>	Shanghai market, early morning buzz</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>We keep us busy believing, ensuring, circling around the corpus (sic)</line>
        <line>	as hyenas approach</line>
        <line>There is no magic, secrets, or hope, or better days or worse days</line>
        <line>THAT is so beautiful!</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>No other than just this:</line>
        <line>Only the fresh sensing,</line>
        <line>the exact cut of grass,</line>
        <line>the smell of rain,</line>
        <line>the spider checking web traffic</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="feeling it" id="feeling-it-129" seq="129" date="2015-09-27" time="21:52" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>All the stuff</line>
        <line>All the noise</line>
        <line>Got full of it</line>
        <line>Reverse gear</line>
        <line>Sad thoughts</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>then simply switched modus operandi</line>
        <line>All pass by as junk in a river</line>
        <line>Going so far upstream</line>
        <line>The source is clean</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>All old junk sold at garage sale to haggling neighbors</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Sitting and glowing in darkness not giving anything a shit but in a smiley fashion :-)</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Just remember to forget past present and future</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="green vampires" id="green-vampires-130" seq="130" date="2015-09-28" time="19:47" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>tumbling in my head</line>
        <line>vampires sucking me from inside</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>see them now</line>
        <line>as my night vision has gotten better</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>those fuzzy green shadows</line>
        <line>trying to lure me into the inferno</line>
        <line>I thought was there</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>never found</line>
        <line>neither</line>
        <line>the right silver bullets to use</line>
        <line>nor</line>
        <line>the right gun</line>
        <line role="turn">- those are for utter cowards and feeble bastards anyway</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>this internal invisible implicit intrinsic indivisible battlefield</line>
        <line>has a terminal flaw:</line>
        <line>It never existed.</line>
        <line>Fluke in the scope.</line>
        <line>The Cold War that never was.</line>
        <line>War game simulated.</line>
        <line>Purgatory with nothing to burn.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>So I let it all be</line>
        <line>when I can</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>And all is good</line>
        <line>all is perfect</line>
        <line>Always was, always will be</line>
        <line>So why even worry about anything, anymore?</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="rt 6364" id="rt-6364-131" seq="131" date="2015-09-29" time="21:09" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>Driving nowhere</line>
        <line>Faster than my shadow</line>
        <line>I pass the lines - - - - - - - - - - -</line>
        <line>Like a cowboy concealing his weapon in the horse’s mouth</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>The monochrome desert 2D landscape opens up</line>
        <line>Active coma forms jellyfish in my head</line>
        <line>Radio white noise</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Clock stops</line>
        <line>Missed minutes and seconds</line>
        <line>Through that tunnel</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>The white lights</line>
        <line>The white horizon</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Amnesia - drawing blanks</line>
        <line>Bleak red moonlight casts hard-to-read shadows on my blank map</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>They played dub music at the gas station</line>
        <line>Strange coke bottles and eight track tapes</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Artesia - what the hell is here? Chaos Cafe closed for eternity</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="relinquish" id="relinquish-132" seq="132" date="2015-09-30" time="23:06" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>Feeling a weird subtle happiness today</line>
        <line>no apparent reason?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>when control is relinquished I guess it happens</line>
        <line>relax in my self, or rather</line>
        <line>relax in not my self</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>feeling each moment extremely clear</line>
        <line>senses very hyper enhanced alerted</line>
        <line>like a new kind of world inside the ordinary one</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>very playful</line>
        <line>on the beach</line>
        <line>big castles of sand</line>
        <line>tide is killing them</line>
        <line>the Beagle is peeing at them</line>
        <line>that is ok</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>as sand castles are mandalas of creation and destruction…</line>
        <line>decay and create…</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>we are working so hard trying to build us one…</line>
        <line>but it is superfluous</line>
        <line>no need</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>no need to make wrong efforts</line>
        <line>only effortless efforts</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>cry a little when it goes to Hell</line>
        <line>but it is fine</line>
        <line>it is part of it</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>nothing really solid - hold your hand anyway</line>
        <line>the impossible crazy love</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="Raymond in Saigon #1" id="raymond-in-saigon-1-133" seq="133" date="2015-10-02" time="22:00" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>Section 1</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>ego in thousand pieces</line>
        <line>the Beagle trying to chew</line>
        <line>but it ain’t tastin’ good</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>trying to pick them up, and sort them by color, best I can</line>
        <line>but it’s hard as they’re all white</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>so I sweep them under the Persian rug</line>
        <line>among all the other pieces</line>
        <line>from all the other years</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Tristan Tzara comes by, suggesting we should burn them in the furnace</line>
        <line>I argue that ego pieces cannot be burned by ordinary means.</line>
        <line>It requires special handling, only known by the Mythical Guru in the Southern Mountain.</line>
        <line>We, including the pissing Beagle (Raymond is his name today), set out to seek and find.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Packing a blanket, some bread, and wine (Raymond is in AA, so no-no for him).</line>
        <line>Walking, far, it is, very tired, very tired. We are all VERY tired.</line>
        <line>So deciding to take off our boots and camp.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Under the blanket I dream about forgotten days in sun &amp; wind &amp; green eyed girls.</line>
        <line>Tristan brings out his chess board, trying to beat Fischer in his sleep.</line>
        <line>Raymond dreaming of his drinking days sniffing all empty bottles in hot pursuit.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Next morning, wondering</line>
        <line>where we are, where we were</line>
        <line>The days we were so sure, and certain</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Bread is soggy and Tristan tries to shave in the reflection from a puddle of dirty water.</line>
        <line>Not working in an optimal way, more of a sub optimal way, or rather stupid, some say,</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I check my hour glass I found in Saigon just after the war. It is in French, so I am never sure.</line>
        <line>Tristan brings out his last piece of Belgian Chocolate, for him to consume in typical snob fashion</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>We three - on the mountain - no clue - what a farce!</line>
        <line>The alcoholic dog leads the way, a scent driving the poor creature, Up and Up!</line>
        <line>There is a house there, an actual house, kind of boring looking</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>And there is a guy inside the house, kind of sad looking, an actual sad guy sitting in his sad house, not doing much.</line>
        <line>Dirty dishes, empty dog food cans, Reader’s Digest, fuzzy dice, paintings of unicorns, cheap shoes.</line>
        <line>He is sipping on a beer with ice.</line>
        <line>His name is Pyle, a very quiet guy.</line>
        <line>We all look at each other in silence.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the guy had his walls covered by black and white photos depicting the same Asian woman</line>
        <line>‘Lustprinzip’ was a word that came out from his mouth, repeatedly</line>
        <line>we were offered to stay overnight</line>
        <line>Raymond slept under the old Grand Piano, dust thick as the Arctic ice shell before global warming</line>
        <line>Tristan &amp; I played poker, a few missing cards, few missing points, no big deal</line>
        <line>fire place cozy light, that crackling sound</line>
        <line>warm beer and too old sardine sandwiches (poor guys on Cannery Row - no laughing any night soon - Verboten)</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>next day we were reborn skeptical - is this the Guru, really?</line>
        <line>Tristan walked back and forth like a copper on the beat. just needing some donuts to complete that picture.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Section 2</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>dreamy clouds passing by dirty windows</line>
        <line>temple bells can be heard</line>
        <line>old donut boxes on the ground</line>
        <line>water falling distant</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>chopping wood</line>
        <line>cleaning rice</line>
        <line>morning gruel</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>black robes</line>
        <line>chanting Chinese</line>
        <line>bells and incense</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>morning drum swirls its tones deep in echo</line>
        <line>cloth touching floor</line>
        <line>traces of turbulent flickering smoke</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Section 3</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Raymond sniffing the ground</line>
        <line>something is there?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the team enters grid search by the book</line>
        <line>square by square</line>
        <line>they sieve the ground</line>
        <line>led by this disastrous Hound</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>they only find old rice</line>
        <line>and remains of some Ancient Spice</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>this is disturbing as Tristan gets thirsty, hot day up in the clouds</line>
        <line>we bring out the guy for a silent picnic on these majestic grounds</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>no one gets the wiser</line>
        <line>crack up my Man!</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line caesura="7">https://www.facebook.com/groups/LionsLairWriters/permalink/1038691516164493/</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="Noch Nicht vorbei" id="noch-nicht-vorbei-134" seq="134" date="2015-10-03" time="21:16" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>strangers on a train meet,</line>
        <line>a little bubble of subjective objective expands,</line>
        <line>nice to meet you,</line>
        <line>burst!</line>
        <line>wet spot,</line>
        <line>soon dry</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>—</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the man had dinner in all quietness - then ordered a ‘B-52 in the Desert’ - boom - all kaputt, no Dessert - man is gone and gone.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>—</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>all questions answered - but no one is happy - the man behind the curtain has to reboot the world again - as we forget each time</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>—</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Our Quiet American in Saigon reports that an hourglass was stolen earlier in the day from Mr Fowler’s collection.</line>
        <line>He is severing all diplomatic ties and will be seen somewhere Tuesdays from hereon.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Any tip that leads to recapture of time stolen will be honored with mentioning and dinner, on the house.</line>
        <line>This is a serious matter according to anonymous sources in the State Department.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Meanwhile, we all have a drink and gossip about the latest, a week old in this godforsaken forgotten part of town.</line>
        <line>Annoyingly hard to get a cab at this hour, as we withdraw to hotel rooms, spider webs and cracked China, dripping faucets.</line>
        <line>The man had dinner in all quietness - then ordered no dessert, no one saw him leave?</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="rough" id="rough-135" seq="135" date="2015-10-04" time="20:14" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>rough day</line>
        <line>distances to everything</line>
        <line>gray skin</line>
        <line>gray skies</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>many steps ahead - so I thought</line>
        <line>but now feel like falling being even more?</line>
        <line>just a static existence</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>passive status</line>
        <line>not forward nor backward</line>
        <line>nothing</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>doors are locked</line>
        <line>right now</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>know it is not real, but surely feels like it</line>
        <line>karmic consequences to here, as well</line>
        <line>so karmic consequences to there, as well</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="strange days" id="strange-days-136" seq="136" date="2015-10-06" time="18:48" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>A couple of strange days</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Dreaming of beagles and dachshunds chasing a shadow.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Being held in darkness hearing a small stream of water</line>
        <line>Oscillating black and white</line>
        <line>Close but not close</line>
        <line>All these counter points</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Daisy flower fields</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>People I thought I knew but I didn’t</line>
        <line>Memories I love, but sometimes hurting too much</line>
        <line>Persons I trusted, they didn’t hear me or I didn’t hear them clearly?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>The weakness of our conventional knowledge</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>The road with barking dogs and shadows and water and daisy flowers - where does it lead?</line>
        <line>Is this an even road to follow?</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="embrace" id="embrace-137" seq="137" date="2015-10-06" time="22:23" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>Ah!</line>
        <line>Embrace it</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>The lemon on the floor</line>
        <line caesura="1">Eat it with pleasure / dirt and all. Squeeze it harder.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Yesterday's jam</line>
        <line>Have it on a cracked cracker found behind the fridge.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Hotel room with broken promises</line>
        <line>Car with no gasoline</line>
        <line>Where to dream tonight?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>The used tea bag - use it again with no prejudice! Second chances my friend.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>The diner with no coffee by the road with no curves.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>The last street light flickered as I tried to make sense of it.</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="embrace II" id="embrace-ii-138" seq="138" date="2015-10-07" time="18:54" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>blue cats in the hotel room</line>
        <line>looking at me</line>
        <line>with accusing green eyes</line>
        <line>what I would do about those teabags and trashed lemons from last night?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>bad sign, these cats following me, last in Saigon</line>
        <line>thought they would be gone</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>The quiet American spying from behind a hole in the wall</line>
        <line>can hear a cigarette lighter going, off and on, off and on</line>
        <line>he is anxious to get out of this, but has to abide in silence</line>
        <line>still a year to go on the contract, before shipped elsewhere</line>
        <line>have been too long in the field</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>a chill, as the temperature drops suddenly, the cats want out</line>
        <line>this is a vortex of weird currents and streams</line>
        <line>time is cooling down, slowing down to a halt</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the world goes by in flickering frames</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="roses" id="roses-139" seq="139" date="2015-10-11" time="20:30" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>also</line>
        <line>the rhythm is good now</line>
        <line>of events following each other as waves</line>
        <line>without consciousness</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>all colors of the rainbow</line>
        <line>gold is not found</line>
        <line>but sensing seismic</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line caesura="2">no past/no present/no future - the killing fields</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the roses</line>
        <line>accompanied by my favorite</line>
        <line>impossible love</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>(Dean: "Favorite impossible love" is super strong. Three words imply what can be impossible to explain while holding significant sentiment. )</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="fluid" id="fluid-140" seq="140" date="2015-10-12" time="19:41" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>icy moment of clarity</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>seeing that I am getting more and more undefined</line>
        <line>lost those urges of knowing what to do, where to go, with whom</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>it is unsettling and contains some anxious vibrations</line>
        <line>but it is also freeing and serene</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the uncertainty as a neutral friend</line>
        <line>being in the Absurd no man’s land</line>
        <line>the DMZ</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>somewhere is a reality maybe</line>
        <line>somewhere there are dreams</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>relaxed &amp; tense &amp; calm &amp; vivid</line>
        <line>being the mandala wiped out after being carefully constructed</line>
        <line>without feeling regret</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>so many spend time on analyzing history - what went wrong, what to learn</line>
        <line>so many spend time on painting pictures of future - what is it going to be</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I am not certain that way of being is optimal</line>
        <line>Anymore</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="NOON" id="noon-141" seq="141" date="2015-10-12" time="22:52" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>German tech NO music</line>
        <line>music for the NO w</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the NO torious</line>
        <line>NO mads of volume</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>making your NO se vibrate wildly</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>NO thing is sacred</line>
        <line>in the NO n-fatal beat</line>
        <line>of  Egotr ON ic</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>ON the other hand</line>
        <line>there is a shake ON time</line>
        <line>ON stage presence</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>making your h ON esty questioned</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the ON slaught</line>
        <line>the ON button pressed hard to the metal</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the opium is ON</line>
        <line>ON wards Comrades!</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="felt" id="felt-142" seq="142" date="2015-10-14" time="20:38" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>felt loving today</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>amongst crocodiles and monsters</line>
        <line>I can see behind their masks</line>
        <line>cut out with Exacto knife</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>loving everything</line>
        <line>a silly feeling with outbursts of energy</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>washed my brain sitting quietly</line>
        <line>listening to songs</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>closing the door to the Darkness outside</line>
        <line>and let</line>
        <line>crocodiles and monsters</line>
        <line>look sad</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="sunflower future" id="sunflower-future-143" seq="143" date="2015-10-14" time="21:20" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>flowing sun-</line>
        <line>flower</line>
        <line>fields</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>forgetting</line>
        <line>fast</line>
        <line>fortunes come and go</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>feasible to grow something new?</line>
        <line>forests and</line>
        <line>foggy lakes</line>
        <line>for purpose of beauty</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>foreclosed expectations</line>
        <line>forever covered</line>
        <line>fields of</line>
        <line>forgetfulness sun-</line>
        <line>flower future</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="yabby you" id="yabby-you-144" seq="144" date="2015-10-15" time="22:43" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>slightly grayish day sitting in the Thule radar station underground wintertime, Greenland work nonstop</line>
        <line>Polar Bears shooting at you - yes they do!</line>
        <line>white ground and the black sky of nothingness around</line>
        <line>big radar goes around and around, barely audible</line>
        <line>see tiny lights of jets landing taking off landing again</line>
        <line>out here there is room for silence tiny bar on base, Bar-biturate, sleepy place for tired souls they play Yabby You</line>
        <line>life at home seems so very distant and unreal what are my friends doing? sad - they closed my favorite coffee shop</line>
        <line>playing some Addams Family pinball dogs sleeping under pool tables they have Ms Pac man too</line>
        <line>life is not moving fast out here, no frames of reference but it is like a retreat from home wherever home might be?</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="to anima" id="to-anima-145" seq="145" date="2015-10-17" time="23:30" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>calm abiding</line>
        <line>the energy is there</line>
        <line>no feeling of anything special</line>
        <line>the habit makes it dull</line>
        <line>instead of seeing the open space</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>how do I talk with my anima</line>
        <line>the female inside</line>
        <line>that I try to project outside</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>that makes ‘her’ look so fascinating</line>
        <line>but that she is not</line>
        <line>like most people and I</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>How do moods come from her?</line>
        <line>But feelings from me?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>did everything</line>
        <line>but not given rest</line>
        <line>the conventional is acting right</line>
        <line>the unconventional not feeling anything</line>
        <line>just sadness</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I do not understand the world</line>
        <line>I do not know the history</line>
        <line>I do not understand the future</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I do not understand why ‘my’ feeling most often do not match with the external?</line>
        <line>It is like a thin layer of darkness wrapped around something</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>So tired of all words and descriptions and theories</line>
        <line>Can I find a resolution at some point?</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="blender on liquify" id="blender-on-liquify-146" seq="146" date="2015-10-18" time="15:19" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>how to really do the hard things you know you have to do?</line>
        <line>the things that you read and hear, and approve of</line>
        <line>things people say</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>to totally reach out of your comfort zone</line>
        <line>and not just for a little bit</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>in this I don’t feel any direction</line>
        <line>no one really seems authentic in this regard</line>
        <line>how to learn something without any guidance?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I think some waypoints passed can’t be un-passed</line>
        <line>the rocks cover the road behind you</line>
        <line>the lava stream obliterating</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>how to really trust?</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="drops" id="drops-147" seq="147" date="2015-10-18" time="20:49" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>black snowballs are thrown after me</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>ripples of small waves permeating</line>
        <line>the atmosphere in the ocean of my emotions</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>positively white snowballs I throw at you</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>crashes of big waves entering</line>
        <line>the shore of silence in my thoughts</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>melting all those snowballs away</line>
        <line>melting my mind now</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>ultimately a black oily spot remains</line>
        <line>rainbow colors reflected</line>
        <line>by rising moon</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>desperately trying to collect mind drops</line>
        <line>counting 1, 2, 3,… aloud as I carefully put them in a tiny blue bottle</line>
        <line>with a cute yellow label</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>making a snowball to throw</line>
        <line>but you are gone</line>
        <line>my mind is gone</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>and now the fresh dark snow falls again</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="beat of the Universes" id="beat-of-the-universes-148" seq="148" date="2015-10-18" time="21:50" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>the beat goes through the shield of frozen water forming ice crystals</line>
        <line>awakening the Empress of Emptiness within</line>
        <line>thawing stiff limbs and rigid mindset</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the beat moves particles</line>
        <line>sparkling in a colorful rain</line>
        <line>as thoughts &amp; emotions &amp; feelings form, and are set free</line>
        <line>chasing each other out on the vast Abstract plains</line>
        <line>in all ten directions</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the beat thrusts</line>
        <line>the love and the search and the sunflowers fields I see far away</line>
        <line>	could be a yellow-green oil pain-thing</line>
        <line>	hanging on a wall</line>
        <line>	people arguing all around</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>still, the beat of awareness</line>
        <line>each note is a new death &amp; rebirth</line>
        <line>as each Universe is replaced by the next</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>and the absolute freedom is always there for us to use</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="chain" id="chain-149" seq="149" date="2015-10-19" time="21:38" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>tears rip</line>
        <line>all hope tied to a weak link</line>
        <line>that one day rusted</line>
        <line>and broke</line>
        <line>fall was high</line>
        <line>impact gruesome</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>‘manufacturing defect’ is not helpful</line>
        <line>lying on the ground</line>
        <line>all dark here</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>crawling around in this diminished capacity</line>
        <line>sore and bleeding</line>
        <line>feeling my way</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>at the bottom of a bottomless pit</line>
        <line>very long way</line>
        <line>very long way from home</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>thoughts run around echoing in this chamber</line>
        <line>until tired</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>when sleep comes, unruly, nightmarish</line>
        <line>I see strange things in the dreams</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>grey light seeps down in the morning</line>
        <line>light rain</line>
        <line>wet and hungry</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>energy is fading</line>
        <line>but there is always a little left</line>
        <line>to survive a little longer</line>
        <line>with</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="hit and miss" id="hit-and-miss-150" seq="150" date="2015-10-20" time="14:53" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>the Angst</line>
        <line>never seems to leave me</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the Stimulation</line>
        <line>that makes me so happy</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the Women</line>
        <line>that are so fascinating</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>but nothing stays</line>
        <line>and falling down hard</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>what choice do I have?</line>
        <line>why do I feel so sad for something that never was real</line>
        <line>it was hope with no promises</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>am I attributing the wrong way?</line>
        <line>altogether</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="tapes" id="tapes-151" seq="151" date="2015-10-20" time="22:24" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>these emotions</line>
        <line>points to the unreality</line>
        <line>mind playing its tape</line>
        <line>over and over</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the tape is playing old songs</line>
        <line>not the songs of today</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>these tapes of love, maybe</line>
        <line>should be put on a shelf</line>
        <line>and not brought back</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>until a day to come</line>
        <line>when it is ok</line>
        <line>to remember</line>
        <line>again</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="single crocodile" id="single-crocodile-152" seq="152" date="2015-10-21" time="19:34" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>Deep within submerged blocks of cement</line>
        <line>tilted in a weird angle</line>
        <line>octopus running away</line>
        <line>glowing rabbit pulsates through the snow</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>this is the way it should have been</line>
        <line>bad memories and lost love</line>
        <line>so, better now, he says and throws a stone in water</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>long lines of metal are directed to the West</line>
        <line>go there and find the treasure, find the new horizon</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line caesura="1">do you think you have a soul/spirit or similar? someone asked me,</line>
        <line>and I realized that I don’t believe I have one with that kind of names</line>
        <line>a dream told me that it is my celestial being</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>this is no good the Professor exclaims!</line>
        <line>all dogs howl at him because no treats tonight</line>
        <line>just retreats in the woods</line>
        <line>fire is burning, cooking beans and old cabbage</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>so the story goes, and it is cold tonight</line>
        <line>fire extinguished</line>
        <line>just a single crocodile is chewing on cheddar cheese!</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="poetry police" id="poetry-police-153" seq="153" date="2015-10-21" time="21:43" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>I want to play the poetry police</line>
        <line>like the old daDas did</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Leninists throw bottles at the Tsar</line>
        <line>secret police knock knock</line>
        <line>I am accused of not doing anything wrong</line>
        <line>except knowing what is not wrong to do</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the police is asking</line>
        <line>for my freedom</line>
        <line>my choice</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>but I cannot respond</line>
        <line>so they put me in a cell</line>
        <line>with a phone for incoming calls</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>waiting</line>
        <line>waiting</line>
        <line>…</line>
        <line>waiting</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>but no one calls</line>
        <line>so sad</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>so sad - I need to write some words</line>
        <line>to enlighten the worlds:</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>‘once upon time there was a Red Communist</line>
        <line>hiding for the Loud Capitalist</line>
        <line>owning only a tiny hammer and sickle</line>
        <line>no chance!’</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>whispering: ‘so there you go’</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="thank you" id="thank-you-154" seq="154" date="2015-10-21" time="21:59" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>my muse is called ‘Celestial Being’ by me</line>
        <line>she is a she (I state)</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>writing these words through my hands</line>
        <line>her wisdom</line>
        <line>her bliss</line>
        <line>her transformations</line>
        <line>her projections</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>coming through</line>
        <line>from infinite skies</line>
        <line>eternal lights</line>
        <line>formless and tiny being</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>thinking I could understand</line>
        <line>but I have to trust her</line>
        <line>with my life</line>
        <line>in her hands</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>else,</line>
        <line>	just an empty shell</line>
        <line>	walking to my job</line>
        <line>	walking home again</line>
        <line>	that would be Death</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>so, appreciation is in its place</line>
        <line>but I think she plays me sometimes</line>
        <line>not sure what do believe</line>
        <line>as her nature is unknown</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>people tell me that I have a soul or spirit</line>
        <line>	but I don’t believe so</line>
        <line>I have something much more subtle and serene</line>
        <line>	a playful and esoteric Celestial Being</line>
        <line>	fooling Death and Birth</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>it is comforting in this visible world to have a friend</line>
        <line>and guide</line>
        <line>that knows the territory</line>
        <line>so to speak</line>
        <line>as ‘she’ wrote :-)</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="john" id="john-155" seq="155" date="2015-10-22" time="20:26" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>oh jazzy john</line>
        <line>naima, africa, spiritual</line>
        <line>listening closer</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>space between tweeting tones</line>
        <line>walking around his landscape</line>
        <line>of music</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>taking a breath</line>
        <line>trying to get deeper</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>solo piano…</line>
        <line>| ||| ||| ||| ||||</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>hearing the bass</line>
        <line>going subtly</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>one disappears into</line>
        <line>for moments</line>
        <line>clarity</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>floating in oceans</line>
        <line>of jazzy</line>
        <line>flow</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="red bull gives?" id="red-bull-gives-156" seq="156" date="2015-10-23" time="21:18" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>monotonic day</line>
        <line>I drove to the store</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>bought a rare drug for me - red bull</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>sat in the park</line>
        <line>by myself</line>
        <line>in the sunshine</line>
        <line>sipping</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>all of a sudden</line>
        <line>brightening</line>
        <line>happiness arising</line>
        <line>feeling the complete synchronization of all tiny specks</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>&amp; I see the stars even in full daylight</line>
        <line>&amp; I see the moons behind the sun</line>
        <line>&amp; I see the water filling the park all the way</line>
        <line>&amp; I see car lights fuzzy navigating the underwaters</line>
        <line>&amp; I see Angels relaxing their wings</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I do not know how red bull is involved with wings and all,</line>
        <line>maybe it was enhanced with magic spells?</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="my my hey hey" id="my-my-hey-hey-157" seq="157" date="2015-10-23" time="21:48" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>fire and flames</line>
        <line>rock and roll can never die</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the cars crusin’ up and down THE Route 6-6</line>
        <line>blasting</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>flashing police lights</line>
        <line>alarms go</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>homeless begging at bus stops</line>
        <line>and traffic lights</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>neon signs</line>
        <line>and broken buildings</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>a scene from breaking bad</line>
        <line>doesn’t have to be arranged</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>understated beauty of ABQ in our heart &amp; horror!</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="red star" id="red-star-158" seq="158" date="2015-10-23" time="22:42" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>Red Star</line>
        <line>in my backyard</line>
        <line>found one day</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>tiny one, alone</line>
        <line>glowing in the dark under some debris</line>
        <line>it had lost its star map and stumbled</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>so I took it in as</line>
        <line>a house guest</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>bathed it in bubbles</line>
        <line>now shining and beautiful Red Star</line>
        <line>staying in my all white guest room</line>
        <line>nice contrast!</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>not certain what it thinks</line>
        <line>about this situation</line>
        <line>if it thinks?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>haven’t been in this exact circumstance before</line>
        <line>no googling helps here</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>doing my best to help it</line>
        <line>so far from its home</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>twinkling sparkling</line>
        <line>Red Star</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>once upon a time</line>
        <line>softly disorganized</line>
        <line>found my backyard</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="opposite of the usual velocity" id="opposite-of-the-usual-velocity-159" seq="159" date="2015-10-24" time="00:21" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>Flow at full brain speed</line>
        <line>Acid natural speed</line>
        <line>Full anarchy bliss go into the bad and kill kill</line>
        <line>Bullets in flight tracers in light</line>
        <line>Don't stop before starting</line>
        <line>Don't stop at the low altitude</line>
        <line>Light source the Death Star gone into memory loss and hunger</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Speed gets the zone in existence excellence</line>
        <line>My life my speed</line>
        <line caesura="2">White lines rushing to form infinite thinness // Big logs untangle and rush downstream</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Yes. Impermanent foundations break.</line>
        <line>No need to need just need the speed and some roads to roam</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="all good Earth" id="all-good-earth-160" seq="160" date="2015-10-24" time="13:31" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>Mission phase. The braking phase (P63) is denoted BR, the approach phase (P64) AP.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>	These beautiful islands</line>
        <line>	Palmtrees</line>
        <line>	Turquoise waters</line>
        <line>	Volcanic black sand</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Applicable point in phase. Inception is denoted I, terminus F, and target point T.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>	Waterfall</line>
        <line>  	Preparing yams at the beach</line>
        <line>	Airport with a welcome band playing</line>
        <line>	Island rhythms</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>A time interval (typically 2.2 seconds) added to the target-referenced time T in P63 and P64 to account for the effective transport lag due to computation and system response times.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>	Airplane with pigs and chicken</line>
        <line>	Take it easy, delay is the norm</line>
        <line>	See the next island appear out of the endless Sea</line>
        <line>	Warm people, smiles</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Terminal - descent phase or terminal - descent-phase guidance program.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>	Final paradise, green rain</line>
        <line>	Mango, papaya fresh</line>
        <line>	Rusty little boat, engine trouble, it is cool Man!</line>
        <line>	River boats, silently gliding</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Actuator born from sweeping lies street cleaner eyes.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>	And it ends on a good note</line>
        <line>	Maybe I will come back, maybe not</line>
        <line>	Dreams and memories remains</line>
        <line>	Regardless of destiny or unfolding of life</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="supreme validation" id="supreme-validation-161" seq="161" date="2015-10-24" time="19:15" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>got to hear good words today</line>
        <line>by someone I adore</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>tear-eyed</line>
        <line>never told by anyone before</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>that my name would be on her gravestone</line>
        <line>out of gratitude</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="sine" id="sine-162" seq="162" date="2015-10-24" time="22:50" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>sine wave getting stuck at the low tone</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>step back a bit</line>
        <line>and watch it</line>
        <line>oscilloscope green line</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>watch it go up by itself</line>
        <line>wu wei</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>follow the dot</line>
        <line>drawing the line</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>spectrum analyzer</line>
        <line>looking for you</line>
        <line>but no finding</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>getting stuck in the image</line>
        <line>burnt into the glass</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>step back a bit</line>
        <line>and watch it</line>
        <line>reflection blinds you</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>melting glass</line>
        <line>sun fire</line>
        <line>plasma - all identity on the loose</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>sine wave reconstitutes itself moving at light speed</line>
        <line>no one watching anymore</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="loss" id="loss-163" seq="163" date="2015-10-25" time="09:26" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>something I knew</line>
        <line>got answered</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>in an honest way</line>
        <line>as I asked the question</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the answer still very painful</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>suffering</line>
        <line>trying to stay with it</line>
        <line>this time</line>
        <line>not escape</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>self compassion</line>
        <line>recycle heart in pieces</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>—</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>looping in my head</line>
        <line>what she said (there is no chemistry)</line>
        <line>something I knew, implicitly</line>
        <line>but different to hear, explicitly</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I keep repeating</line>
        <line>in my head:</line>
        <line>images, words, thoughts, memories</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>need to get force from the DADA:</line>
        <line>flower butter hound switch blade red green yellow steel bridge</line>
        <line>all is mixed in my head, all is mixed up nothing is clear all is unstable all is confusion</line>
        <line>tiny dogs barking in my head, tiny cats meowing cactus</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>—</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>we have been friends all along, really</line>
        <line>I hoped something else</line>
        <line>but got openings now and then, to leave</line>
        <line>I didn’t take them</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>but is this sorrow just that?</line>
        <line>something I really knew for months, or more</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>just fleeting emotions</line>
        <line>feeling sad</line>
        <line>lonely</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>but I know it wasn’t always like this</line>
        <line>it won’t always be like this</line>
        <line>I have someone liking me</line>
        <line>I have friends</line>
        <line>I have new interests</line>
        <line>I have therapy</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I know some will be stirred up, now and then</line>
        <line>I need self-compassion though</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>but I did things myself too…</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I shouldn’t play myself down for this (since May)</line>
        <line>why did I go on pretending when she was clear?</line>
        <line>but all time together was mostly nice, so hard to appreciate when it is not more</line>
        <line>what is it I was looking for?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>but I got told good stuff too</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="sorry!" id="sorry-164" seq="164" date="2015-10-26" time="22:01" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>sorry for all poems written</line>
        <line>it is the best I can do</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>it is hard for me to explain how the writing is done</line>
        <line>‘I’ really don’t create anything - and that it is not a joke, I repeat</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>people ask for intentions, words, images, line breaks</line>
        <line>sorry, I just don’t know</line>
        <line>nothing is ‘designed’ for any particular purpose in Mind</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I read it after the fact, trying to decipher maybe</line>
        <line>your theory is as good as mine</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>it is one way to express beyond ‘my self’</line>
        <line>trying to realize (never understand) a shadow of what is beyond ‘my self’</line>
        <line>trying to emphasize other realities beyond our crude language constrained world</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>my quote:</line>
        <line>“suddenly fragments and triggers uncover themselves and writing commences,</line>
        <line>but the unknown intention was already in place”</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>not my quote:</line>
        <line>“I speak only of myself since I do not wish to convince, I have no right to drag others into my river, I oblige no one to follow me and everybody practices his art in his own way."</line>
        <line role="turn">- Tristan Tzara "Dada Manifesto 1918”</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="getting something" id="getting-something-165" seq="165" date="2015-10-26" time="22:32" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>in a blink,</line>
        <line caesura="1">duration of a 1/100 finger snap</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>‘see’</line>
        <line>one frame of a world, one world</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line> ‘see’</line>
        <line>birth</line>
        <line>death</line>
        <line>in Light</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>‘see’</line>
        <line>dissolved</line>
        <line>not annihilated</line>
        <line>in Dark</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>beyond ‘beyond nomenclature’</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>laughter</line>
        <line>joy</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>‘seeing’ persisted?</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="oh bella notte" id="oh-bella-notte-166" seq="166" date="2015-10-26" time="22:52" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>throw stone into pond - splash!!!</line>
        <line>rapid ripples</line>
        <line>moon disturbed reflection</line>
        <line>settles reluctantly</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>spooky</line>
        <line>	owl screams</line>
        <line>	bats hover stealthy</line>
        <line>in moist and raw cooling air</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>tired of, trying to sleep</line>
        <line>little mosquito won’t</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>—</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line caesura="1">cut up (10/27 22:06)</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>and raw rapid ripples</line>
        <line>little mosquito hovers stealthy</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>throw stone raw cooling disturbed reflection</line>
        <line>sleep little pond - won't moon disturbed</line>
        <line>stealthy in splash!</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>scream reluctantly bats trying to air</line>
        <line>tired mosquito went in moist settles!</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>spooky owl trying cooling air</line>
        <line>reflection settles - splash to sleep</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="emergence" id="emergence-167" seq="167" date="2015-10-27" time="21:36" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>Pressure is on to scatter ego</line>
        <line>Another way to see</line>
        <line>Emotion implosion</line>
        <line>Feelings burst</line>
        <line>Memory images maxed and mixed</line>
        <line>Repeat loop until diminished</line>
        <line>Messing with various levers</line>
        <line>Non-linear thought</line>
        <line>Focus will widen bigger</line>
        <line>Where is the compassion?</line>
        <line>Decrypt and desist</line>
        <line>High maintenance mind</line>
        <line>Kaleidoscope - looking too close into the emerging patterns</line>
        <line>Volatile - one of a kind - Voilà!</line>
        <line>Alchemic Brujería looking sinister: apocalyptic - where will the caterpillar go?</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="acid - 199 bpm" id="acid-199-bpm-168" seq="168" date="2015-10-28" time="21:29" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>hyper creativity</line>
        <line>the cheapest drug there is</line>
        <line>with free love of all included</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>mind warp drive</line>
        <line>lineage back before my face was born</line>
        <line>don’t touch the chime scene!</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>joy laugh bliss</line>
        <line>this bastard back to the caves of Cthulhu</line>
        <line>Molok eats the Howling Ginsberg for lunch</line>
        <line>    and the homework stolen from dogs and lawyers</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>levitating Tibetan Tulkus Cultivating the Empty fields</line>
        <line>crash cymbals and horns and Yak butter greasing my wheels of dharma</line>
        <line>Shambhala is fast forwarding now reaching touch point of vortex</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>let acid house deep leaks</line>
        <line>of wikis burning</line>
        <line>journalists’ noses on habanero fire escape</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Brigato Rosso kidnaps Aldo Moro</line>
        <line>watching Red Desert</line>
        <line>swimming in Loch Ness</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>can I get some windows in this house???</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="acid - e-xit" id="acid-e-xit-169" seq="169" date="2015-10-28" time="22:02" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>trance shamanic maglev quark e-xpress</line>
        <line>intersecting North and South</line>
        <line>|—|</line>
        <line>|—|</line>
        <line>singing old songs from the folks way back when</line>
        <line>drumming double vision blurred blue brews</line>
        <line>crawling through hollow roots</line>
        <line>looking for e-xit signs</line>
        <line>phone wires disconnected</line>
        <line>|—|</line>
        <line>|—|</line>
        <line>Raven throwing careful eyes at the spectacle</line>
        <line>beneath: ah - these humans…</line>
        <line>|—|</line>
        <line>|—|</line>
        <line>crystal lakes flavors of viola red white polka candy</line>
        <line>melting the pot of white phosphor</line>
        <line>easy to the touch there, chef!</line>
        <line>|—|</line>
        <line>|—|</line>
        <line>no need for E-mergence yet</line>
        <line>time is still to come</line>
        <line>catching up old memories</line>
        <line>reflections in mirrors thawed,</line>
        <line>entrenched in permafrost</line>
        <line>|—|</line>
        <line>|—|</line>
        <line>as the rail is built</line>
        <line>fast enough</line>
        <line>will it leave the station</line>
        <line>before the train?</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="Opus DEI" id="opus-dei-170" seq="170" date="2015-10-29" time="21:03" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>red spectrum light was faded</line>
        <line>hardly got through</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>but</line>
        <line>gotten stronger abiding its time</line>
        <line>growing</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>light turning blue spectrum</line>
        <line>prism is placed in front</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>refraction in multiple directions</line>
        <line>probing the Dark Ether Investigation - Opus DEI</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>each spectral range deployed to search and destroy</line>
        <line>remains of my ragged soul</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>lying in the scorching desert sun wondering where  I am</line>
        <line>radio telescopes searching for my Inert Spectral Body</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>meanwhile,</line>
        <line>trying feverishly to design</line>
        <line>very large array reverse prism Matrix</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the One that will collect</line>
        <line>all those rays</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>into One</line>
        <line>the hyper-sharp laser beam</line>
        <line>piercing through mind, matter</line>
        <line>into final Emptiness Abode</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="blue for two" id="blue-for-two-171" seq="171" date="2015-10-29" time="21:51" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>beach house</line>
        <line>spring</line>
        <line>open the windows</line>
        <line>fresh air though all rooms</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>lapis lazuli blue necklace</line>
        <line>found on the white night stand</line>
        <line>dusty mirror</line>
        <line>will ask someone to clean it later</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>it was a sad memory that came back</line>
        <line>these tiny details</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>she was a hesitant love</line>
        <line>never entirely sure</line>
        <line>but capturing my affection</line>
        <line>regardless</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>it was a happy memory that came back</line>
        <line>these tiny details</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>she was an adventurous love</line>
        <line>Dana Point</line>
        <line>Big Sur</line>
        <line>Santa Cruz</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I got her that necklace as a gift before it all turned</line>
        <line>regardless</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>she told long after that the neckless always reminded her about me and my blue eyes</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>so I got the same one to have as a bittersweet memory generator</line>
        <line role="turn">- all the happy and all the sad</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>but we can’t never now before hand</line>
        <line>as the caterpillar can’t know it will become a butterfly?</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="acid - mystical star and spiders" id="acid-mystical-star-and-spiders-172" seq="172" date="2015-10-29" time="22:35" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>awakening</line>
        <line>this red island</line>
        <line>thin drizzle purple drops touching my face</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>silence in illumination</line>
        <line>charcoal characters crawling closely</line>
        <line>they escaped from my prints but lost colors</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I sense movement nearby</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>unicorns?</line>
        <line>or giant spiders?</line>
        <line>or lemon beagles?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I sense fear</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>start chanting in Sanskrit</line>
        <line>I light my cigarette lighter, previously owned by Harry Truman</line>
        <line>having Danish Æbleskiver for dinner</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I sense calm</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>nothing there</line>
        <line>except a blue light</line>
        <line>the light from the Mystical Star</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="clear and restless danger" id="clear-and-restless-danger-173" seq="173" date="2015-10-30" time="20:22" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>so tired of hyper thinking</line>
        <line>mind is energized</line>
        <line>craving and grasping for something</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>it is clear</line>
        <line>but restless</line>
        <line>thoughts come and go</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>fear of silence?</line>
        <line>causing Existential Angst to be felt more deeply?</line>
        <line>some call it samsara</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>fear that nothing got resolved today?</line>
        <line>that it will never be resolved</line>
        <line>all the power I have, not being shared?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Mu!</line>
        <line>Laugh!</line>
        <line>Ha!</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>have to practice going into this point</line>
        <line>like and dislikes pulls and pushes</line>
        <line>clearly, ‘I’ exists too much</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>my lack of validation is lack of trust?</line>
        <line>lack of feeling it?</line>
        <line>or yet another construct</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>some people make me relaxed and soothed</line>
        <line>no problems trusting then,</line>
        <line>leaving the bigger context</line>
        <line>why can’t I be relaxed on my own?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>all my practice?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>(Tulku pg 123)</line>
        <line>If awareness doesn’t choose a goal toward which energy can be directed, energy becomes inconsistent, chaotic and confused, and eventually turns toward dullness.</line>
        <line>Energy without concentration is scattered and restless: instead of being productive, it feeds on dissatisfaction and tends toward extremes of emotionality and ultimately collapse.</line>
        <line>Without energy, awareness and concentration are quickly depleted; if they do continue to operate, we fall into daydreams or pleasant and essentially meaningless images.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>So Adderall works by increasing concentration :-)</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Releasing concentration feels directly negative.</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="unlayered" id="unlayered-174" seq="174" date="2015-10-30" time="22:18" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>they are after me</line>
        <line>the shadows</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I feel Presence</line>
        <line>dissolving me</line>
        <line>in a glass of water</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>piece by piece</line>
        <line>burnt with magnifying glass</line>
        <line>sunny lazy afternoons</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>each layer broken</line>
        <line>opens the next World</line>
        <line>to investigate</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I feel Fear</line>
        <line>diminishing</line>
        <line>squashed with fire extinguisher</line>
        <line>white foam all over</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>can’t do a legal U-turn anymore</line>
        <line>trying to shake the shadows tailing me</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="reworked (not publish)" id="reworked-not-publish-175" seq="175" date="2015-10-30" time="22:50" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>Katrena Roach</line>
        <line>October 28 at 10:25am</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>"In my dreams,</line>
        <line>we are dancing in a field</line>
        <line>time has slowed</line>
        <line>or ceased to exist.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>You and I-</line>
        <line>running free,</line>
        <line>the only two hearts beating,</line>
        <line>beating to our own rhythm,</line>
        <line>chasing dandelion wishes,</line>
        <line>always searching,</line>
        <line>searching for the soul</line>
        <line>that fits back with mine,</line>
        <line>for the air that fills my lungs,</line>
        <line>just out of reach,</line>
        <line>exhausted, breathless,</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I slowly wilt,</line>
        <line>back into the dirt.</line>
        <line>I awake alone. "</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>—</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>In the Final War</line>
        <line>we hide by the Killing Fields</line>
        <line>time running out</line>
        <line>like fuse sparks approaching gasoline</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>you and I</line>
        <line>burning yellow bright</line>
        <line>the only life remaining</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>in the ashes raining</line>
        <line>covering the black car skeleton</line>
        <line>K-9 searching for survivors</line>
        <line>stepping on mines</line>
        <line>poor dogs &amp; people!</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>dust fills our lungs</line>
        <line>inhaling radioactive particles</line>
        <line>work their way in</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I slowly fall down</line>
        <line>back into the dirt</line>
        <line>I die alone</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="crash" id="crash-176" seq="176" date="2015-11-01" time="21:31" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>now I am exhausted</line>
        <line>by all thoughts</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>crashing down like a plane with broken engine</line>
        <line>it will survive this time I am sure</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>it is just too much confusion</line>
        <line>scared of not knowing</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>all the burden on me with no real support</line>
        <line>no one really listening deep</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I know this is not real - it is a emotional state for a short while - wait out each wave of it</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>all the theories but no resolution</line>
        <line>feels nice to write</line>
        <line>but what to really do?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>how do I get new air to breathe?</line>
        <line>how do I find the map again?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I think I have developed</line>
        <line>keep saying that</line>
        <line>but have I really?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>what are lies, denial, truth?</line>
        <line>can I see though feelings and not get dragged down by them</line>
        <line>being ok being aware only?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>how do I pull through without validation this time?</line>
        <line>how do I keep sanity being fragile?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the practice of facing and embracing when it is hard</line>
        <line>the practice of going on under this hard ship</line>
        <line>the practice of releasing old ideas</line>
        <line>really sailing with uncertainty</line>
        <line>don’t expect help, but appreciate help</line>
        <line>why can’t I do what I need to do?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I torture myself with what has been and could have been, but didn’t become</line>
        <line>I torture myself expecting short term working fixes</line>
        <line>Tired of writing all of this.</line>
        <line>Tired of not getting anywhere at all.</line>
        <line>Doing and doing, but expecting something back when there is no one there.</line>
        <line>Why can’t I know what to do?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Tired of not getting tractions, tired of not having power enough, not wisdom enough.</line>
        <line>Tired of all practice that doesn’t apply.</line>
        <line>Tired of feeling down.</line>
        <line>Tired of listening.</line>
        <line>Tired of hearing.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Tired of not having a working approach.</line>
        <line>Tired off asking maybe, and to not have any certainty.</line>
        <line>Tired of being fragile.</line>
        <line>Tired of my emotions up and down.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Tired of this big wall in front of me.</line>
        <line>Tired of never knowing anything.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Maybe this great suffering can push me.</line>
        <line>Tired of being this serious.</line>
        <line>Tired of missing people and animals that I loved.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Tired of being less than optimal.</line>
        <line>Tired of looking.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I know this is samsara.</line>
        <line>I know this is impermanence.</line>
        <line>I know this is not lasting.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>But how do I live it authentically?</line>
        <line>How do I release the focus on myself?</line>
        <line>How do other people deal with it?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Tired of the ego grasping and hoping.</line>
        <line>Tired of burning cycles writing this, but what to do instead?</line>
        <line>Tired of talking, texting, emailing.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Why can I never feel good about myself by myself.</line>
        <line>How to reach the surface behind emotions &amp; feelings &amp; thoughts?</line>
        <line>Why do I need to ask all the questions?</line>
        <line>Why can’t anyone answer any of them?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Why can’t I accept what is in a better way?</line>
        <line>I simply hate this state so much, never seems to be able to avoid it.</line>
        <line>I don’t feel it helps to describe or analyze so much.</line>
        <line>But where is the real anger and tears hidden?</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="positive thinking" id="positive-thinking-177" seq="177" date="2015-11-01" time="22:38" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>tired of thinking</line>
        <line>tired of talking</line>
        <line>tired of waiting</line>
        <line>tired of understanding</line>
        <line>tired of observing</line>
        <line>tired of these feelings</line>
        <line>tired of writing about this</line>
        <line>tired of expecting</line>
        <line>tired of avoiding</line>
        <line>tired of blandness</line>
        <line>tired of average</line>
        <line>tired of the comparison</line>
        <line>tired of being told ‘it is all good.'</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>tired of my leaking tire</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>tired of searching in cold places for old cases</line>
        <line>tired of the sameness</line>
        <line>tired of theory and its explanations</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>tired of being told ‘after rain comes the sunshine.'</line>
        <line>After the moon comes star shine?</line>
        <line>Tired of my shoes getting wet on the streets of San Francisco</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>tired of people explaining to me</line>
        <line>tired of order</line>
        <line>tired of trying to fit in and then tired when I won’t and then tired of thinking about it</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>tired of dogs howling at fire trucks passing</line>
        <line>tired of the ambulance helicopters flying by</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>tired of the lack of compassion and lack of wisdom</line>
        <line>tired of the lack of knowledge and lack of true appreciation</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>tired of having time to watch</line>
        <line>tired of my coffee maker I don’t use, why not give it to Goodwill?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>tired of grasping and attaining when I know it is stupid</line>
        <line>tired of saying: “saying is not doing.”</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>tired of the surface</line>
        <line>tired of people saying they are creative, but are not</line>
        <line>tired of art that looks like something</line>
        <line>tired of people saying they like art doesn’t look like something, but they don’t</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>tired of expectations that I knew would not be met and then get disappointed when the expectations were not met</line>
        <line>tired of saying ‘I understand.'</line>
        <line>really tired of people saying ‘ok, true, bless you, I wish, I hope.'</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>tired of all information</line>
        <line>tired to hear life was simple in the old days</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>time to yawn and go to bed I think!</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="negative thinking" id="negative-thinking-178" seq="178" date="2015-11-02" time="07:23" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>like charcoal on my hands and face and feet</line>
        <line>like marzipan snowballs I make and swallow so quickly no one can see them</line>
        <line>like True Meaning of Dub</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>like Lucky Luke drawing faster than his shadow</line>
        <line>like Milou’s (Snowy’s) optimism</line>
        <line>like toll roads without cash or cards</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>like Finnish real wood fired Sauna, jumping in the snow</line>
        <line>like an old Land Rover Series II with alpine windows</line>
        <line>like the new snow without a trace yet</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>like people talking about chess games in Central Park</line>
        <line>liked Bobby Fischer before he went crazy</line>
        <line>like black and white tile floors, Buddy Holly’s glasses lying on an old newspaper in one corner</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>like old castles filled with ghosts and iron maidens getting’ ya’!</line>
        <line>like old Zen monks with no teeth but a toothbrush</line>
        <line>like when the lakes are freezing, and the sound when the ice is cracking later</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>like wet leaves and dogs resting on them</line>
        <line>like the black lava land</line>
        <line>like the relaxed conversations at gas stations here in NM</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>like the coffee at the Marina in Dana Point</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>like when I can realize my path is my path, I can do what I want -</line>
        <line>like it or not!</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="ice breaker" id="ice-breaker-179" seq="179" date="2015-11-04" time="19:41" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>like charcoal smudged on my hands and face and feet</line>
        <line>lying down in the forest</line>
        <line>dirt</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>how did I get here?</line>
        <line>remember rolling in wet leaves and teasing dogs resting on them</line>
        <line>remember wood fired Sauna</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>remember, in the winter…</line>
        <line>… the lakes are frozen and icy, drifting my car in circles</line>
        <line>… new snow without a trace yet</line>
        <line>… jumping in the snow</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>now the sound of ice melting and cracking</line>
        <line>walking over it</line>
        <line>cracks behind me</line>
        <line>have to run</line>
        <line>haven’t seen this side of the lake before</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>remember…</line>
        <line>… the sausage and beer</line>
        <line>… the laughter</line>
        <line>… the heat and steam</line>
        <line>… the drunken walk</line>
        <line>…the square in the ice, to jump into</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>a tiny house in the opening</line>
        <line>smoke &amp; light &amp; movement &amp; barking</line>
        <line>someone comes out looking around carefully</line>
        <line>our eyes meet, and it is a peculiar moment</line>
        <line>not hostile, kind of recognition, curiosity</line>
        <line>she invites me</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>remember…</line>
        <line>… the ice fishing</line>
        <line>… the long cross-country skiing into the dark</line>
        <line>… the dark winter roads with no cars</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>she is silent</line>
        <line>and takes out her drum</line>
        <line>starts drumming</line>
        <line>trance is coming, can’t resist, no choice</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I see…</line>
        <line>black and white</line>
        <line>tile floor</line>
        <line>a newspaper in the corner of the room</line>
        <line>from February 3rd, 1959</line>
        <line>glasses lying on top, like the ones Buddy Holly had</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I see…</line>
        <line>red and white</line>
        <line>table cloth</line>
        <line>Christmas napkins</line>
        <line>the smell of glue wine</line>
        <line>and smoked eel</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I see…</line>
        <line>yellow and white</line>
        <line>dress</line>
        <line>a woman</line>
        <line>with a certain gaze</line>
        <line>not hostile, kind of recognition, curiosity</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="impermanence" id="impermanence-180" seq="180" date="2015-11-04" time="19:56" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>coming and going</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>so much happened</line>
        <line>so much came</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>so much disappeared</line>
        <line>yet again</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>wondering if this cycle will end</line>
        <line>I know it won’t</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>would be nice with an illusion of stability and permanence</line>
        <line>I know it ain’t</line>
        <line>happening</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the wind is strong out there</line>
        <line>walking fast to avoid the cold</line>
        <line>a frozen house</line>
        <line>finding firewood</line>
        <line>soon warmth spreads</line>
        <line>I hear the wolves howl</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>one day the winter is coming to end</line>
        <line>and I’ll be going somewhere yet again</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="freedom" id="freedom-181" seq="181" date="2015-11-04" time="20:56" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>missing sun</line>
        <line>and a paradise island</line>
        <line>dune buggy flying in a dust cloud</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>saxophone solos</line>
        <line>and, of course, the reggae beat</line>
        <line>brewing food in aluminum foil deep down in the sand</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>ice cold drinks</line>
        <line>people relaxed teasing joking</line>
        <line>throwing frisbees and stuff around</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I have been to places like that</line>
        <line>might not have happened in exactly this way</line>
        <line>but close enough to remember today</line>
        <line>when the sun is missing</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="clowns" id="clowns-182" seq="182" date="2015-11-04" time="21:19" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>angry clowns chasing me…</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I am sitting here in this tiny house</line>
        <line>thinking I am afraid of clowns (which I am not)</line>
        <line>wondering how it would feel</line>
        <line>every time I saw one?</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="war" id="war-183" seq="183" date="2015-11-05" time="22:21" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>struggle conflict tension</line>
        <line>volatile thoughts ever changing</line>
        <line>that is me</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>it drives crazy creativity</line>
        <line>thriving on change and transitions</line>
        <line>but</line>
        <line>sometimes I wish for some stability</line>
        <line>even if I know, it is an illusion</line>
        <line>feeling grounded for a moment</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>it won’t last long though</line>
        <line>as the honest and authentic life for me is in groundlessness</line>
        <line>unfolding, really, not just saying</line>
        <line>freedom is fearful at times</line>
        <line>I know this, always been like it</line>
        <line>but it is hard, at times very hard</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I just can’t get that epiphany:</line>
        <line>That is what I want to do!</line>
        <line>This is where I want to live!</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>lived in rural areas, islands, cities, different countries</line>
        <line>married, divorced, dogs, cats, houses, cars, jobs</line>
        <line>passion, love, failed love, storms</line>
        <line>followed the wind where it took me</line>
        <line>sure, nostalgia and memories are certainly there</line>
        <line>but I would never go back to try again</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>being a Zen Buddhist, this all makes sense, though:</line>
        <line>impermanence, emptiness</line>
        <line>maybe I am the embodiment of what I want to be, at the core?</line>
        <line>I just can’t or won’t accept it yet; it is fearful</line>
        <line>something is pushing me, an invisible friend or enemy?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the day I surrender waving the white flag</line>
        <line>the day of absolute clarity and absolute calmness will come</line>
        <line>and then there is no doubt</line>
        <line>then I will know</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>but until then,</line>
        <line>the struggle goes on</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="watch it" id="watch-it-184" seq="184" date="2015-11-05" time="23:18" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>blue cats yellow eyes</line>
        <line>staring through mailboxes</line>
        <line>&amp; us</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>periscopes through manholes</line>
        <line>spying on you</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>watching</line>
        <line>as you go to sleep</line>
        <line>don’t forget to close all windows</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>electric eyes</line>
        <line>behind every door</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>vaults lock you up</line>
        <line>no visitation rights</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>night visionaries running</line>
        <line>behind walls</line>
        <line>walls of sleep</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="adjust" id="adjust-185" seq="185" date="2015-11-05" time="23:30" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>to be adjusted</line>
        <line>got it all wrong</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I am looking out with an agitated mind</line>
        <line>creating all worlds</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I am falling for distorted emotions</line>
        <line>pulling me down</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>just go on</line>
        <line>go in</line>
        <line>inside outside</line>
        <line>where the music play</line>
        <line>happy</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>just go on</line>
        <line>go out</line>
        <line>outside inside</line>
        <line>where it is grey &amp;</line>
        <line>sad</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>in calmness</line>
        <line>there is no inside outside</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>fractured moments</line>
        <line>each one</line>
        <line>piece of mind</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>in clarity</line>
        <line>emotions &amp; feelings of no use</line>
        <line>thoughts not working any more</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>can feel it oscillate back and forth</line>
        <line>the writing is reflected and reflecting?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>stage is to reach endless confusion</line>
        <line>what to trust?</line>
        <line>what to believe?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>no wind</line>
        <line>no fire</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>adjusting…</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="screen print" id="screen-print-186" seq="186" date="2015-11-06" time="21:05" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>sun rising today</line>
        <line>shaky start</line>
        <line>gotten better and better</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>so happy I am out of it</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="simply morning" id="simply-morning-187" seq="187" date="2015-11-07" time="11:11" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>sun &amp; cold</line>
        <line>windy morning</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>my spirit was high from the get go</line>
        <line>no idea why</line>
        <line>simply happy :-)</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>awesome - it comes when stop trying</line>
        <line>sadness leaves when you stop trying</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>but forcing any of it fails</line>
        <line>the more force the more fail</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line caesura="1">going beyond the negative/positive in to simply Being</line>
        <line>then it is all good</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="slowness" id="slowness-188" seq="188" date="2015-11-07" time="22:16" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>started good</line>
        <line>slowed down</line>
        <line>got dark</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>out of synch with time</line>
        <line>thinking</line>
        <line>not not-thinking</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>derailed</line>
        <line>same tracks every day</line>
        <line>trying to build new bridges</line>
        <line>bridges to nowhere?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>so in my head</line>
        <line>can’t get out of it</line>
        <line>how do I not think?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>so sad for what did not happen</line>
        <line>so sad for being lost</line>
        <line>so sad for no one calling</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>how did I end up here</line>
        <line>supreme lack of stimulation</line>
        <line>I am stuck in ice, melting slowly</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>so strange</line>
        <line>I have friends and interests</line>
        <line>but it still feels empty</line>
        <line>or is it just detox?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>just feel that no one is missing or needing me</line>
        <line>no connection</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>there is a connection when there is a live connection</line>
        <line>but it fades quickly</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line caesura="1">the connection to something/someone gives meaning</line>
        <line>disconnect means jumping mind</line>
        <line>connect calm mind</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="my path" id="my-path-189" seq="189" date="2015-11-08" time="16:49" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>my path</line>
        <line>I thought was shrouded</line>
        <line>by extensive forests &amp; mountains &amp; clouds</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>no line of sight</line>
        <line>no GPS signal</line>
        <line>white pebbles marking the way been lost (as in that X-Files episode)</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I felt I ‘ought’ to know</line>
        <line>grew up without directions or guidance</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>left a sense of being lost at sea</line>
        <line>cotton in my ears</line>
        <line>misty smoke</line>
        <line>green, red lanterns switched off</line>
        <line>lighthouse keeper went to bed</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>left to my own devices, I made decisions</line>
        <line>bringing me to this exact point</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I realize there is no comparison with anyone else’s path</line>
        <line>no one to ask for directions - they will say something nice and point somewhere</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I have to embrace the fact</line>
        <line>that I am standing with my snowshoes at the end of the travelled path</line>
        <line>traces soon to be wiped out</line>
        <line>on this white snow field with a storm whipping the crystals in my face</line>
        <line>it hurts and bleeds</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>simply have to go on</line>
        <line>as the path was never shrouded</line>
        <line>it never existed</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="into my senses" id="into-my-senses-190" seq="190" date="2015-11-08" time="20:17" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>when that moment of drop comes</line>
        <line caesura="1">the moment focus is lost/momentum thrown out of the window (now broken window)</line>
        <line>restlessness enters its dirty Gestalt</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>looking around trying to grasp for something</line>
        <line>thoughts try to grasp and crave</line>
        <line>a way out of it</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>this reaction hardens the patterns</line>
        <line>like a body in cement</line>
        <line>won’t wake up</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Mu!</line>
        <line>the corrective action is unprecedented action - follow the first instinct, no second thoughts</line>
        <line>stop and enter your senses</line>
        <line>only sensing</line>
        <line>breathe</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>and the new world appears fresh</line>
        <line>all traces of the old gone</line>
        <line>if done wholeheartedly</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Ad infinitum…</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="force" id="force-191" seq="191" date="2015-11-09" time="19:37" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>when I let me down, below</line>
        <line>in the cellar</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>when the monster comes behind me</line>
        <line>to direct a blow</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>then be still</line>
        <line>be calm</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the intense life and death presence</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="until next" id="until-next-192" seq="192" date="2015-11-10" time="19:44" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>never know when…</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>suddenly she appears again</line>
        <line>takes me by surprise every time</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>she is standing close, with a certain deep blue eyed gaze, saying ‘hi, darling’</line>
        <line>that immediate rushy &amp; sparky feeling in the gut, and sudden warmth</line>
        <line>so unexpected</line>
        <line>no layers of protection, surge from nowhere</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>been like this, a brief contact, a nimble spark, and then she is gone</line>
        <line>and I forget</line>
        <line>until next time</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>akin to  having a very exquisite dessert in an unexpected place in the middle of nowhere</line>
        <line>a sweet memory, but won’t find it again, and I shouldn’t look for it, leave it at that</line>
        <line>it exists somewhere out there and in me, but hidden for the time being</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>suddenly she appears again</line>
        <line>we did get a chance to talk for the first time</line>
        <line>we are going to meet</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>that is all good</line>
        <line>but I hope the delicate mystery will not be gone</line>
        <line>because the uncertainty, instinct and wonder is subtle and hearthwarming</line>
        <line>the knowing is distinct and sometimes brutal</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="saint ann" id="saint-ann-193" seq="193" date="2015-11-10" time="20:59" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>for all real and imaginary Rastafarians &amp; Lions &amp; King of Kings…</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>we are in Babylon</line>
        <line>outside our Home</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>on tour in Hell</line>
        <line>far from Saint Ann Parish</line>
        <line>the rolling green hills</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Nine Miles to walk</line>
        <line>Nine Miles to cry</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the water falls empty into the Sea</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>in the distance you can hear</line>
        <line>the music evoking and invoking</line>
        <line>words spoken thus:</line>
        <line>‘Jah Jah protect mi fram mi enemy dem’</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="hyper flow" id="hyper-flow-194" seq="194" date="2015-11-11" time="18:22" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>wow, when all stars align…</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>deep into creative and hard problems</line>
        <line>eight hours passes as nothing, day after day</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>this is the melting core</line>
        <line>the bliss and joy</line>
        <line>to immerse into</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>everything else simply does not exist</line>
        <line>might sound extreme</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>some call it peak experience</line>
        <line>some call it flow</line>
        <line>being in the zone, (I call it the Interzone)</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>this is raw power</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>there is no person anymore</line>
        <line>only fusion</line>
        <line>intensity</line>
        <line>clarity</line>
        <line>purity</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>just to feel this now and then</line>
        <line>makes it easier to breath</line>
        <line>when things are not going well</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the One Mind truly creates all</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="space" id="space-195" seq="195" date="2015-11-11" time="19:35" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>wish there was a Space</line>
        <line>to hangout</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>with dadaist friends</line>
        <line>and others</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>writers, crazies, artists</line>
        <line>like me</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>all have our blemishes and burns</line>
        <line>life as it comes</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>non-conventional unconventional extremes</line>
        <line>fluid thoughts and words</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>would be easier when ‘coming out’ to the ‘real’ world again</line>
        <line>wouldn’t feel so odd and unreal</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>but who is really after the core?</line>
        <line>and to just saying it?</line>
        <line>am I?</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="andrea mc3 letter 1" id="andrea-mc3-letter-1-196" seq="196" date="2015-11-13" time="17:32" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>(Write a goodbye letter to an expectation that has run its course and is now passing. Acknowledge it. Respect it, even if it no longer belongs to you. Say your goodbye. Let it go.)</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>It has been a wonderful acquaintance that grew and grew, my hopes started to grow too, This magnificent and unconventional woman. I felt so relaxed and easy in your presence.</line>
        <line>I know there where warning signs, and that you were never clear about our relationship, but I kept hoping, emotionally. At times I had doubts, rationally. The summer past and there were bad moments, I felt it was over, but not entirely, Guess the hope was there, maybe based on nostalgia and my expectations.</line>
        <line>We met again after your illness,  and my feelings came back. So that day I asked you straight, you answered surprised: 'no, there is no chemistry between us'.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Been suffering in waves since, but it is time to acknowledge that my expectations were in my mind only, they don't belong there, and should vanish over time.</line>
        <line>So thanks for the juice and Good Bye!</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="andrea mc3 letter 2" id="andrea-mc3-letter-2-198" seq="198" date="2015-11-13" time="17:33" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>(What is your dark side? What do your demons look like? And how can you use them to your benefit, instead of hiding them in your closet?  Write them an acceptance letter. Hire them as assistants to your Wholeness.)</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>My demon is the demon of idleness (Idle Daemon). I am not functioning well without appropriate stimuli, I get restless and unfocused, the mind starts grasping, and negativity comes up.</line>
        <line>So I am writing to accept the fact that you might exist in my mind, and I have tried not to see you when you arrive into Me. I am the Host, and you are the Guest, you are welcome to stay as you please!</line>
        <line>The benefit is to use your Presence as a reminder of impermanence, Mara and decay, needed for continued creation. Embrace the necessity of this down time as a rest area or pit stop. Refuel, reignite, recycle and reconnect.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Hereby, I wanna sniff some wheatgrass and hire you as my Assistant to the Regional Manager.</line>
        <line>Yours Truly - the Interzone Daemon</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="phx delay" id="phx-delay-199" seq="199" date="2015-11-15" time="21:42" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>I like airports</line>
        <line>ambient noise &amp; movement</line>
        <line>calm stillness-oasis in me</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>feeling being grounded (Major Tom?)</line>
        <line>home more than 'home'</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>delays don't matter</line>
        <line role="turn">- any aggression is created by you and no one else</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>floating in salt water tank</line>
        <line>wide eyes shut open</line>
        <line>by the Dead Sea</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>hearing all destinations called out</line>
        <line>final call, Closing Call</line>
        <line>the old days with the sound of the board changing</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>where do you want to go today, man?</line>
        <line>guess I am restless by birth</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>when I land I rent a car and drive West,</line>
        <line>sleep at some motel with that chemical smell</line>
        <line>have yucky coffee, and plastic Danish</line>
        <line>see the Pacific, Pacific Mon Amour, in the morning</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>as life &amp; death</line>
        <line>going on into infinity</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>passing the noise of doubts and habits and time and sky and stars and darkness in the deep Ocean</line>
        <line>all memories so far away</line>
        <line>fading as patterns in sand dunes ever moving</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>passing the words of friendly remarks</line>
        <line>being freed from prison of hearing how it should be</line>
        <line>freed from hearing others whine and complain about loss and gain - all empty anyway</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>drinking my cold Evian, alpine smooth water</line>
        <line>my last preference and attachment</line>
        <line>before stopping my search</line>
        <line>for the Gate</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="grains" id="grains-200" seq="200" date="2015-11-15" time="22:33" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>all fleeting in senses</line>
        <line>creating me as I were</line>
        <line>a while ago</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>little spider hiding</line>
        <line>rain drops</line>
        <line>worries</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>all same importance</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>dog snoozing</line>
        <line>one eye half open</line>
        <line>blink</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>skin hot &amp; sandy</line>
        <line>beauty &amp; death &amp; rotting corpse</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>all same importance</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>we are so thin on top of sensing</line>
        <line>the mind, the story, the narrative</line>
        <line>based on no real evidence</line>
        <line>desperately searching or thinking we are not</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>real time blinks</line>
        <line>chunks coming and going</line>
        <line>entering &amp; leaving</line>
        <line>flashing lights on blue metal machine</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>all same importance</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>love &amp; hate &amp; winning &amp; losing</line>
        <line>no difference</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>life is what is pulsating now</line>
        <line>death is what is pulsating now</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line caesura="7">nothing to do with ego/person/self/me/you/individual/soul/spirit</line>
        <line>those are just wastes of time</line>
        <line>in the very small and very grand scheme</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>we are tiny grains in death</line>
        <line>in life we are fleeting as dust in the wind</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="needs" id="needs-201" seq="201" date="2015-11-16" time="09:11" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>No need</line>
        <line>No need to grasp or find</line>
        <line>No need to hide</line>
        <line>No need to compare</line>
        <line>No need to need</line>
        <line>No need to believe</line>
        <line>No need to despair</line>
        <line>No need to hope</line>
        <line>No need</line>
        <line>Nope and No!</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="chaos order" id="chaos-order-202" seq="202" date="2015-11-16" time="20:41" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>intention?</line>
        <line>what is my intention?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>home?</line>
        <line>where is my home?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>attraction?</line>
        <line>what attracts me specifically, and not?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>‘hereness’ - about what is here and now, and who is here, and who is not here?</line>
        <line>how it is here right now</line>
        <line>not how it was over there some other time</line>
        <line>what is the connecting tissue?</line>
        <line>what of real importance exists at this moment, here?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>‘thereness’ - about what comes from remote locations</line>
        <line>who is there? why did they do it? whom to punish? why are they stupid? why are we right and smart?</line>
        <line>Republicans, Terrorists, Democrats, Paris, Lebanon, Timothy McVeigh, Drones, Good intentions, Solidarity</line>
        <line>Where is compassion, and why is it replaced by anger? And why is that question angering further?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>‘thusness’ -</line>
        <line>not here - not there</line>
        <line>not then - not later - not now</line>
        <line>no one is here</line>
        <line>no one was here or will be</line>
        <line>only ever flowing inconceivable</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>locking in</line>
        <line>not being or creation</line>
        <line>intention?</line>
        <line>home?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>words like ‘light’ ‘space’ mean something experienced not thought</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="flat lining" id="flat-lining-203" seq="203" date="2015-11-17" time="08:50" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>flat lining this morning</line>
        <line>not depressed, but completely fed up</line>
        <line>it is an emotion, is there a sense starting it?</line>
        <line>grey, cold, no sleep</line>
        <line>a jumble of thoughts come up, some newer, good and and, some older. why her? why so strong memories? need to be saved?</line>
        <line caesura="1">I keep grasping/reaching, not connected to anything. Just mind in circles. Exactly.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>—</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line caesura="1">This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self. The Buddha implies here that this statement can be used as an antidote to our habitual “I-making” and as a means of penetrating reality as it is. That is, by cultivating the understanding that “this perception (or material/body, feeling, conceptual fabrication, cognizance) is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self,” we begin simultaneously to weaken our sense of self and see how things really are—devoid of self, essence, spirit, or soul.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>arise - persist - dissolve - disappear</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Sutra 6</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>It is important to note that the Buddha is not denying the reality of each of these processes. He is merely clarifying the nature of their realness. In our everyday speech, don’t we use “real” to indicate qualities of absoluteness, continuity, solidity, fixedness, and so forth? That sensation you feel on touching a hot cup of coffee is a real, felt sensation. There is no denying the fact. But in what sense is it real? The Buddha’s examples seem intentionally to run counter to our common assumptions about the nature of “real.” Like a water bubble, a feeling of “hot” arises when the necessary conditions are present; persists as long as these conditions hold together; dissolves as those conditions weaken; and disappears as they disintegrate. Why is this insight important? You can do an experiment. Practice viewing appearances, perceptions, feelings, conceptualizations, and thoughts in the manner recommended by the Buddha here. Is your habitual way of reacting altered at all? What qualities of being become present when you see forms as balls of foam and thoughts as magical illusions? When you view reality in this manner, what then?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>feeling: sensation -&gt; emotion</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>disenchanted. When we unconsciously, unquestioningly view some object as being just as it “appears” to us, or just as we perceive it (and so on with the other khandhas)—in some objective, absolute sense—this view is evidence that we are enthralled or enchanted by the appearance, perception, and so on. The Buddha asks at the end of each section, in effect: Why do you persist in being caught up in the endless barrage of appearances, ideas, images, concepts, viewpoints, perspectives, judgments, and so on and on and on? The slow dawning that all of these things are like mirages or magical illusions or hollow tree trunks engenders a clear-eyed disillusionment, disenchantment, and loss of infatuation. No longer infatuated, we naturally experience a dispassionate withdrawal from our habitual involvement with these endless forms. This withdrawal is liberating; it frees us from our previous life-limiting enthrallment. When we are no longer held in thrall (from Anglo-Saxon thræl, “slave”), what then?</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="heart-mind ache" id="heart-mind-ache-204" seq="204" date="2015-11-17" time="15:20" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>“In Chinese philosophy, xin can refer to one's "disposition" or "feelings" (Chinese: 心; pinyin: xīn), or to one's confidence or trust in something or someone (Chinese: 信; pinyin: xìn). Literally, xin (心) refers to the physical heart, though it is sometimes translated as "mind" as the ancient Chinese believed the heart was the center of human cognition. For this reason, it is also sometimes translated as "heart-mind". It has a connotation of intention, yet can be used to refer to long-term goals.”</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>so tired of reading and thinking about</line>
        <line>so tired of writing about</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>need to get down to depths and bliss</line>
        <line>I can do it</line>
        <line>I have done it</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>my intent is to use unprecedented action to decay and create bliss</line>
        <line>I wrote that</line>
        <line>I need to do it, to realize it</line>
        <line>I wrote that</line>
        <line>why can’t I get out of the loop</line>
        <line>into the beautiful world?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>always locked into a prison I don’t belong in anymore</line>
        <line>need to stop theory</line>
        <line>I always need to do something</line>
        <line>but never do</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I keep persisting and persevering</line>
        <line>asking and asking</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>no real intent</line>
        <line>easy to write</line>
        <line>easy to draw</line>
        <line>easy to create</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I have felt love</line>
        <line>but I don’t feel now</line>
        <line>everything amplified</line>
        <line>grasping</line>
        <line>desiring</line>
        <line>trying to rationalizing</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I never jump</line>
        <line>and no one ever listens</line>
        <line>does it matter what I do relative what is proper</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I escape in the zendo, some rest</line>
        <line>rest of the day is suffering, between short periods of focus</line>
        <line>but wrong mood leads to wrong focus</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>what does surrender mean</line>
        <line>why this pain</line>
        <line>why can’t I live free of it</line>
        <line>samsara - I know</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I did all wild things, but ‘grew up’</line>
        <line>where is it now</line>
        <line>why it is hiding</line>
        <line>something is telling me something, do I listen deeply, or just hear</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>three wonderful women in a year, and nothing worked</line>
        <line>probably normal. but so hard to take</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>no connection</line>
        <line>only prison</line>
        <line>no money</line>
        <line>no safety</line>
        <line>no family</line>
        <line>no dog</line>
        <line>no good house</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I don’t have anything to lose</line>
        <line>but I still don’t do anything (well, I do)</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>how to intensify embrace turn the lamp inward</line>
        <line>I know I can be very generous and helping in a certain mood</line>
        <line>why did she open that up? love? attention?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>do I need attention? do I need someone to start a conversation, and not me chasing</line>
        <line>all is broken</line>
        <line>but it is broken at this point</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>isn’t writing a tool to rebuild? am I writing to ‘dry’</line>
        <line>meta meta</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I do feel for Leah though</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I can associate</line>
        <line>I can joke</line>
        <line>but need attention and relaxation, and she gave it sometimes, someone who saw me.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>need someone to see me?</line>
        <line>see my being (miss your Being :-))</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>don’t need more books</line>
        <line>need commitment to something</line>
        <line>need intent</line>
        <line>need focus</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>don’t need all directions</line>
        <line>this writing is proof, my writing is proof</line>
        <line>I can’t sustain anything: marriage, same job, writing long, playing guitar</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I am hard on myself though</line>
        <line>and my name is perseverance</line>
        <line>but how to soften the suffering just a little?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>OR, this is a necessary purge?</line>
        <line>am I too extreme for a relationship</line>
        <line>how do I surrender to myself completely</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I just don’t know or do I know?</line>
        <line>there is emptiness and impermanence</line>
        <line>how do I cope</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>how do I recover my serenity</line>
        <line>my relationship were doomed from the get go, matter of time</line>
        <line>am I too negative</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>wabi-sabi</line>
        <line>Angst</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I am sequencing but not really rational</line>
        <line>hyper intelligent</line>
        <line>but not emotional</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>hate sitting stuck</line>
        <line>need external to move but I have to live myself</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>it is mind and attitude</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>maybe working, writing, drawing, sitting is all I can do</line>
        <line>how to expand</line>
        <line>how to challenge</line>
        <line>how to unstuck</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>need to get down, need to get down!</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>— part II</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>all is poetry</line>
        <line>all is art</line>
        <line>all is koan</line>
        <line>all is mystical</line>
        <line role="turn">- see now</line>
        <line>all energy is good</line>
        <line role="turn">- changes</line>
        <line>all is playful</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>— part III</line>
        <line>Child hood memories</line>
        <line>Long dark hair</line>
        <line>Experience in mind counts not what actually happened</line>
        <line>Counting breaths helps</line>
        <line>Things feels much better</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Is my mind simply full of mystery</line>
        <line>Write fun and pretty</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="summer diving" id="summer-diving-205" seq="205" date="2015-11-17" time="21:40" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line caesura="1">funny fear/agua salá</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>tonight I Totally Recalled a childhood memory</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>spent two whole summer breaks on the Swedish West coast</line>
        <line>rough and rocky shores</line>
        <line>sea anemones cutting the skin</line>
        <line caesura="1">eleven/twelve years old</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>so scared of the deep and dark Atlantic waters (as they say: you won’t be merry on a North Sea ferry)</line>
        <line>especially Phaeophyceae made me nervous - lurking down there</line>
        <line>crabs hiding beneath</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the rough cliffs steep and vertical into the water, so dark and deep</line>
        <line>I didn’t dare to jump</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>—</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the funny thing is</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>next summer I just walked straight out on the scariest cliff and dove straight down into the Sea</line>
        <line>without an ounce of hesitancy</line>
        <line>into the deep and dark</line>
        <line>with all the now harmless and stinking Phaeophyceae - the silly crabs running in panic</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>all days that summer -</line>
        <line>diving</line>
        <line>snorkeling</line>
        <line>floating in a rudderless rubber raft</line>
        <line>getting burned by jellyfish of the nasty kind</line>
        <line>almost started a forest fire Summer Solstice eve</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>and falling in love, at a distance,</line>
        <line>with the beautiful girl Michaela,</line>
        <line>only remember she had long black hair</line>
        <line>but the courage failed me that time</line>
        <line>still waiting for her</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line caesura="3">(Fittingly enough check out https://youtu.be/ukrxIZR2RNY)</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="meetings" id="meetings-206" seq="206" date="2015-11-19" time="06:42" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>You -</line>
        <line>mirror me</line>
        <line>charcoal dark</line>
        <line>light and bright</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Morning Star -</line>
        <line>cold and bright</line>
        <line>early rise</line>
        <line>South Western sky</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Buddha statue -</line>
        <line>gold and bright</line>
        <line>mirrors us</line>
        <line>waking up</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I found a Chinese Buddhist monastery outside of Taos. Not open for the public, but I talked to them and met the head monk this morning (at the Thai Temple in ABQ). I am welcome to attend a three day retreat with them later. Had a nice breakfast with all the monks :-)</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="black metal" id="black-metal-207" seq="207" date="2015-11-19" time="19:31" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>drawn into the Satanic distortion of</line>
        <line>chainsaw massacre guitar riffs</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>The living dead return behind</line>
        <line>bass lines</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>corn man and boogeyman</line>
        <line>haunting your dreams</line>
        <line>waking up shaking to</line>
        <line>even worse fear:</line>
        <line>	your own cold case file</line>
        <line>	dropped behind the shelves</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>drums marauding the pentagram</line>
        <line>burn the crosses</line>
        <line>buried up side down</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>zombie voodoo masters drinking green liquid</line>
        <line>at midnight</line>
        <line>moon behind clouds</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>invoking backwards</line>
        <line>mantra</line>
        <line>calling for Armageddon to commence</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>coming to Earth</line>
        <line>to take revenge</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Overlord of The Universe!</line>
        <line>Lucifer - save me!</line>
        <line>Demon est Deus inversus</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line caesura="3">(https://youtu.be/NBNo3c4ez58)</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="events" id="events-208" seq="208" date="2015-11-19" time="19:57" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>out of synch</line>
        <line>but it is good</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>all overload</line>
        <line>all chaos</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>disconnect from this world</line>
        <line>reconnect to another</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>isolated events</line>
        <line>connected intuitively</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>a doll in a doll in a doll</line>
        <line>a starfish laughing hysterically</line>
        <line>running after the Sun</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>flowing in disruption</line>
        <line>discontinuity as the path</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>all mind blown</line>
        <line>all cover undercut</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>asynchronous timing</line>
        <line>fractures and fractals</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>dog chasing its tails its tail</line>
        <line>jellyfish sunbathing</line>
        <line>running after its cell phone</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>all out of synch</line>
        <line>but it is good</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="no thing" id="no-thing-209" seq="209" date="2015-11-20" time="18:20" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>right now zero</line>
        <line>zero everything</line>
        <line>or maybe vaguely above zero</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>slipping</line>
        <line>today nothing works</line>
        <line>anger</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>take me away</line>
        <line>was good</line>
        <line>now bad</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>relative crazy</line>
        <line>no base</line>
        <line>no line</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="sober" id="sober-210" seq="210" date="2015-11-21" time="21:21" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>sober feeling</line>
        <line>not super good</line>
        <line>not super bad</line>
        <line>focused</line>
        <line>feel active stability</line>
        <line>feel hope</line>
        <line caesura="1">hope of bliss (which is outside of happy/sad)</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="holding too tight" id="holding-too-tight-211" seq="211" date="2015-11-22" time="19:35" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>oh,</line>
        <line>stuck in a vacuum</line>
        <line>feel so small tonight</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>extreme focus</line>
        <line>just me here</line>
        <line>me here on Earth</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>not much communication</line>
        <line>all slow</line>
        <line>some hope</line>
        <line>maybe, maybe</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>equanimity?</line>
        <line>mind loops back as always always always</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I do and can reach out but feel so small tonight</line>
        <line>like it doesn’t help</line>
        <line>but this is exactly when to work it</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>need to stay in what is in</line>
        <line>without trembling else it will always be</line>
        <line>this strangling stress I get into</line>
        <line>not giving any space or light around it</line>
        <line>not using my skillful means for it</line>
        <line>expecting someone to do it</line>
        <line>expecting how it would be</line>
        <line>expecting the external to rule</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I have so much force, but not used to using it</line>
        <line>I want to see my own light!</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>holding too tight</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="mind fuck" id="mind-fuck-212" seq="212" date="2015-11-22" time="21:18" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>completion</line>
        <line>total burn to ashes</line>
        <line>deeply</line>
        <line>beyond categories</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>can’t write it</line>
        <line>can’t say it</line>
        <line>can’t think it</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>white phosphor burn</line>
        <line>mind falling back to mind</line>
        <line>me &amp; I falling on my self</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>emergency EXITs not lit up</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>at the edge of breath</line>
        <line>the edge of reason is far behind</line>
        <line>the edge of advise is far behind</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>keep repeating myself endlessly</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="break" id="break-213" seq="213" date="2015-11-24" time="21:25" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>everything lately makes me positively tired</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I feel no pain</line>
        <line>but turbulence</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>things happening</line>
        <line>overwhelming</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>actually felt content where things are</line>
        <line>today</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>simplicity</line>
        <line>walking the dogs by the river</line>
        <line>no theories, history or future</line>
        <line>no expectations</line>
        <line>but meet again</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>like I reached a knowing</line>
        <line caesura="1">without more input/output</line>
        <line>release and rebirth</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="flurry" id="flurry-214" seq="214" date="2015-11-25" time="20:59" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>day in a flurry</line>
        <line>odd feeling creeps in</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>feeling of something falling into place</line>
        <line>readjusted</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>can’t pinpoint</line>
        <line>it creates a buffer of space</line>
        <line>buffer of light around</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>knocking…</line>
        <line>another door is opened</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>no one else needs to exist for me to be in bliss</line>
        <line>that has been the crux of the matter</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>so now I allow anything to happen</line>
        <line>doesn’t matter what</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>long - short</line>
        <line>cold - warm</line>
        <line>ugly - pretty</line>
        <line>poor - rich</line>
        <line>high - low</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>of no consequence</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>this day creeps into bed</line>
        <line>turning light off</line>
        <line>in a flurry of small stars perambulating</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="orange ocean" id="orange-ocean-215" seq="215" date="2015-11-25" time="21:10" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>red spectrum light was faded</line>
        <line>hardly got through</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>but</line>
        <line>gotten stronger abiding its time</line>
        <line>growing</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>light turning blue spectrum</line>
        <line>prism is placed in front</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>refraction in multiple directions</line>
        <line>probing the Dark Ether Investigation - Opus DEI</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>each spectral range deployed to search and destroy</line>
        <line>remains of my ragged soul</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>lying in the scorching desert sun wondering where  I am</line>
        <line>radio telescopes searching for my Inert Spectral Body</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>meanwhile,</line>
        <line>trying feverishly to design</line>
        <line>very large array reverse prism Matrix</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the One that will collect</line>
        <line>all those rays</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>into One</line>
        <line>the hyper-sharp laser beam</line>
        <line>piercing through mind, matter</line>
        <line>into final Emptiness Abode</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="agent o" id="agent-o-216" seq="216" date="2015-11-25" time="21:33" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>Quiet American</line>
        <line>afloat</line>
        <line>on the Orange Ocean</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the cruiser</line>
        <line>speeding along</line>
        <line>gray sea</line>
        <line>oblique waves heave</line>
        <line>white inferno of ocean spray</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>hidden coordinates</line>
        <line>no lights on</line>
        <line>covert mission</line>
        <line>finding the truth out there</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>anchor point coming up</line>
        <line>light at land sweeping scanning</line>
        <line>fog is our friend</line>
        <line>the rendezvous point</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>he is gliding in the Zodiac</line>
        <line>closing in</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>temple bells chiming</line>
        <line>as he slowly moves inland</line>
        <line>suddenly a dog is barking, so close, too close</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>wait a minute</line>
        <line>he recognizes the dog now</line>
        <line>it is Raymond the pissing Lemon Beagle</line>
        <line>so They are here</line>
        <line>already</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="all your yeahs" id="all-your-yeahs-217" seq="217" date="2015-11-26" time="23:15" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>plugging away to Neverland far away and</line>
        <line>here at the same time</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>crystals slowly forming</line>
        <line>invisibly</line>
        <line>the creation</line>
        <line>to be put offshore into the Orange Ocean</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>treading water and slowly submerging</line>
        <line>down where air bubbles get so big</line>
        <line>sonar pings</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>dark journey under water</line>
        <line>nearing its end</line>
        <line>see the lightness above</line>
        <line>surface breaks</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Neverland rising</line>
        <line>I walk ashore to find my friends</line>
        <line>so this rendezvous could occur</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>having a picnic</line>
        <line>in the shade</line>
        <line>fire cracking</line>
        <line>roasting chestnuts</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>playing with cigarette lighters</line>
        <line>empty bottles</line>
        <line>books by the Ancient Dadas</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>what remains is to be seen</line>
        <line>meanwhile,</line>
        <line>feeling the pulse slowing down</line>
        <line>lying under stars and stripes</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>dreamland comes all blue hues</line>
        <line>soft and still</line>
        <line>utter calmness and serenity</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>in the dream I can hear distant temple bells</line>
        <line>in the dream I can levitate</line>
        <line>I hear the Tibetan horn: ‘It is a long, deep, whirring, haunting wail that takes you out somewhere beyond the highest Himalaya peaks and at the same time back into your mother's womb.’</line>
        <line>I see a white dog playing hide and seek with someone I cannot see</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>as for now that is all I can recall</line>
        <line>it is the sign-off</line>
        <line>another day wakes up from dreams</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="bubbles" id="bubbles-218" seq="218" date="2015-11-28" time="13:48" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>fusion with each fleeting moment</line>
        <line>embrace the whole sensorium</line>
        <line>the forged link</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>moment by moment</line>
        <line>before thought</line>
        <line>in our natural habitat, or domain, our home</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>wholeheartedly</line>
        <line>burning completely</line>
        <line>leaving no ashes</line>
        <line>no traces, like the clouds, passing by</line>
        <line>the energy is neutral</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>it is a high-speed reincarnation</line>
        <line>failure to embrace will have the lingering smell</line>
        <line>’sticky objects’ as Sartre said it</line>
        <line>nausea of sticky objects</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>foot in cactus needles</line>
        <line>or</line>
        <line>foot in dog poop (reminds me about what Baudelaire had to say on that subject)</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the trick is that each moment needs a different embrace</line>
        <line>because it is unique even if it might be similar (yeah, snowflakes, fingerprints)</line>
        <line>only being very calm and clear makes it possible</line>
        <line>equanimity is bliss, and bliss is not happiness; bliss is outside of emotions and feelings</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>‘unprecedented action’ as Andréa Balt calls it, is close</line>
        <line>how to act in a fresh and new way, moment by moment</line>
        <line>being very ‘silent’ is the only way to open the situation</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the action in each moment is influenced by all your wisdom, and ignorance</line>
        <line>the microscopic time slot of freedom still available</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>just a blink too late causes blame, excuses, ‘bad luck’, and all the other ways we use to avoid our responsibility to flow with it</line>
        <line>then we spend endless time analyzing, wallowing, ruminating, feeling unhappy, ‘understanding’ in a limited sense</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>everything IS much simpler than we THINK</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="five elements" id="five-elements-219" seq="219" date="2015-11-28" time="17:03" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>amidst the raging storm</line>
        <line>I can feel it, the danger, the force</line>
        <line>Air - intense aliveness</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>in the turbulent white water rushing river</line>
        <line>I can immerse into the cold and fresh</line>
        <line>Water - intense embrace</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>in the steaming strong emotions</line>
        <line>I can go into them, no fear or doubt</line>
        <line>Fire - intense connection</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>in the desert landscape, driving endlessly</line>
        <line>I can disappear into it</line>
        <line>Earth - intense awareness</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>but my sorrow is</line>
        <line>coming home after an active day</line>
        <line>Space - sometimes makes me nostalgic and melancholic</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I never try to numb it, or escape from it</line>
        <line>maybe I am too impatient, too used to activity, but not busyness</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>my Chinese name is Chuan Nai, ‘transformation and perseverance’</line>
        <line>I keep looking for that inconceivable gate</line>
        <line>it is close, but I have not located it exactly</line>
        <line>can hear it move in the wind</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I do know I have to lose myself completely and disappear into the Darkness to find the gate</line>
        <line>it is just so hard when no one truly understands that</line>
        <line>it is so hard without a deep compassion</line>
        <line>it is scary to enter the stream, knowing ‘I’ cannot ever return as ‘me’</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>want someone to tell me ‘it is ok’, but of course, no one can ever do that</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>air, water, fire, earth and space</line>
        <line>together as one</line>
        <line>but when?</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="freezing moon" id="freezing-moon-220" seq="220" date="2015-11-29" time="00:11" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line caesura="2">Luciferus monster vision / green lights sweeping by / death pushing you down</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line caesura="2">Diabolic hunt after your mind / flat lining screams / dragging body around</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line caesura="2">Craving night demons / scratching your eyes / brain disassembly defunct</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line caesura="2">Freezing moon death chamber / last you see until / dark eats your soul</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line caesura="2">Emptied vessel frozen blood / capture essence of life flame /  reset to zero</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>(Enjoy responsibly with ‘De Mysteriis Dom Sathanas’ - ‘Freezing Moon’)</line>
      </stanza>
      <image src="spooky.jpg"/>
    </poem>
    <poem name="221B life eternal" id="221b-life-eternal-221" seq="221" date="2015-11-29" time="23:02" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>life eternal</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>slow piano tune in the distance</line>
        <line>washed out vacation pictures from way back when</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>old greasy newspaper found in the basement</line>
        <line>used to hide those old WW-II era shells</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>posters with now-forgotten artists</line>
        <line>and celebrities</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>radio with vacuum tubes, glowing nicely at dusk</line>
        <line>before lights are switched on</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>bamboo pen, dried ink</line>
        <line>Chinese scroll</line>
        <line>what is the story therein?</line>
        <line>where are the hidden treasures?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>entering the Chinese landscape</line>
        <line>inside and beyond</line>
        <line>to search for dragons and tigers</line>
        <line>the beautiful mountains</line>
        <line>emanating in the morning</line>
        <line>as fog lifts</line>
        <line>heron white in the water</line>
        <line>all silent</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>black dressed woman walking with a horse across the field</line>
        <line>I better hide, can feel the fear in my gut</line>
        <line>she passes slowly, deep in thoughts</line>
        <line>suddenly stops and looks up</line>
        <line>straight at me</line>
        <line>oh no!</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="naked and not famous" id="naked-and-not-famous-222" seq="222" date="2015-11-29" time="23:30" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>naked in all nakedness</line>
        <line>raw and pure pulse</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>blood hot fever</line>
        <line>sinking down in ever-accelerating delusion</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>tropical sky endlessly blinding</line>
        <line>my weakening soul</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>flawless sky infinite rays piercing</line>
        <line>my beaten spirit</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>volcanic stones cutting my skin</line>
        <line>as I stumble</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>red and clear blood drops</line>
        <line>as I fall</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>it is</line>
        <line>fine though</line>
        <line>balancing between life and next</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>it is</line>
        <line>calm though</line>
        <line>as the future is now singularity</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>red line is thinning</line>
        <line>grinning a little as</line>
        <line>yellow mango fresh</line>
        <line>I find</line>
        <line>shadow and stillness</line>
        <line>brief respite</line>
        <line>moment of taking a breath</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>a woman I never saw before</line>
        <line>she promises to take me to the water - in the next life</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Hush don’t cry as it is time to go</line>
        <line>I better lay my dead flowers all in a row</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>(Inspired in part by the Beach House song ‘All Your Yeahs’)</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="sweeper" id="sweeper-223" seq="223" date="2015-11-30" time="23:51" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>hyper sensitivity</line>
        <line>never thought</line>
        <line>that was it</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>six senses</line>
        <line>on alert</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>unfiltered</line>
        <line>boiling simmering freezing</line>
        <line>stew is on</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>guest in and out</line>
        <line>host impatient too much so</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>‘there is a true man of no rank’</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>all senses are optimal</line>
        <line>no ground is found</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>vacate silence for ’silence’</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>now all can come</line>
        <line>all can go</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>no bother</line>
        <line>no birth</line>
        <line>no death</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="control" id="control-224" seq="224" date="2015-12-01" time="20:15" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>the comfort of no words</line>
        <line>of silence</line>
        <line>slowly</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>cracks in the facade showing themselves</line>
        <line>realizing the need to do the work, the hard work</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>it is easy to discuss and observe</line>
        <line>giving and receiving advice and concepts</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>all of it is useless in practice</line>
        <line>in realization</line>
        <line>pieces of garbage smelling in the sun light</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>nothing can be fixed</line>
        <line>no hope can fix</line>
        <line>no one else can fix</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>nothing needs to be fixed</line>
        <line>but there is still a dead body dead weight</line>
        <line>obscuring the sight</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>if you need to go ’there’ to find ‘here’ then</line>
        <line>this will be a long winter…</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="lighter" id="lighter-225" seq="225" date="2015-12-01" time="20:31" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>it is lighter</line>
        <line>this day</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>lighter deep inside</line>
        <line>maybe not outside</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>following along as the waves go</line>
        <line>as the leaves fall and die</line>
        <line>as the sun beams don’t leave any marks</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>act as semipermeable membrane - letting less through, but not all</line>
        <line>act as centrifuge - separating light and heavy</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>no need for angels, gods, or demons, spirits or souls</line>
        <line>throw all those away</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>and it will be light,</line>
        <line>so light</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="follow" id="follow-226" seq="226" date="2015-12-01" time="22:00" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>follow</line>
        <line>what comes</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>leave</line>
        <line>what goes</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>desire what is given</line>
        <line>in front of you</line>
        <line>only now</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>what is at hand</line>
        <line>not what might become</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>follow the lead of Darkness</line>
        <line>grab the hand</line>
        <line>leading you</line>
        <line>past mine fields</line>
        <line>fires</line>
        <line>storms</line>
        <line>green eyed monsters</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>love the water</line>
        <line>love the Earth</line>
        <line>rainbows and mirage cities</line>
        <line>unicorns and miraculous space ships</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>our own importance is exceptionally small in this</line>
        <line>an atom in a drop in the ocean</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>follow the waves</line>
        <line>as they go</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>leave the water</line>
        <line>as it goes into sky</line>
        <line>forming clouds</line>
        <line>creating drops</line>
        <line>falling</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="no advise" id="no-advise-227" seq="227" date="2015-12-01" time="22:27" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>feel the sphere of fire</line>
        <line>expanding</line>
        <line>stars &amp; emotions</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>in Neverland they grow</line>
        <line>as water falls into the space</line>
        <line>left between breaths and tigers</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>blueberries in the winter</line>
        <line>look so cold to me</line>
        <line>as they forgot about time &amp; seasons</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>as the wind slowly fades</line>
        <line>and the sky is black and dotted</line>
        <line>little cat shivering seeking cover</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>flip the switches for now</line>
        <line>closing all doors</line>
        <line>for the last time</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>ice breaking</line>
        <line>hurry to the port</line>
        <line>ship departs only once</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the infinite Orange Ocean</line>
        <line>with its magic islands</line>
        <line>beaches and unknown treasures &amp; ghosts &amp; despair &amp; life</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="tears for no reason" id="tears-for-no-reason-228" seq="228" date="2015-12-01" time="22:58" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>I have tears</line>
        <line>happy tears</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>from somewhere</line>
        <line>unknown</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>no discernible reason</line>
        <line>no trigger</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>just tears coming out</line>
        <line>wonderful &amp; spontaneous &amp; instinctive</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>not because of anything or anyone</line>
        <line>the source of sorrow &amp; joy is never far from home</line>
        <line>don’t give anyone else that responsibility and weight</line>
        <line>it can never be taken away</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>no thoughts or concerns</line>
        <line>just natural awareness and tears</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="mixed and mixed" id="mixed-and-mixed-229" seq="229" date="2015-12-02" time="20:58" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>Saudade is the recollection of feelings, experiences, places or events that once brought excitement, pleasure, well-being, which now triggers the senses and makes one live again. It can be described as an emptiness, like someone (e.g., one's children, parents, sibling, grandparents, friends, pets) or something (e.g., places, things one used to do in childhood, or other activities performed in the past) that should be there in a particular moment is missing, and the individual feels this absence. It brings sad and happy feelings all together, sadness for missing and happiness for having experienced the feeling.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Sehnsucht represents thoughts and feelings about all facets of life that are unfinished or imperfect, paired with a yearning for ideal alternative experiences. It has been referred to as “life’s longings”; or an individual’s search for happiness while coping with the reality of unattainable wishes. Such feelings are usually profound, and tend to be accompanied by both positive and negative feelings. This produces what has often been described as an ambiguous emotional occurrence</line>
        <line>It is sometimes felt as a longing for a far-off country, but not a particular earthly land which we can identify. Furthermore there is something in the experience which suggests this far-off country is very familiar and indicative of what we might otherwise call "home". At other times it may seem as a longing for a someone or even a something. But the majority of people who experience it are not conscious of what or who the longed for object may be, and the longing is of such profundity and intensity that the subject may immediately be only aware of the emotion itself and not cognizant that there is a something longed for.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Mono no aware, literally "the pathos of things", and also translated as "an empathy toward things", or "a sensitivity to ephemera", is a term for the awareness of impermanence, or transience of things, and both a transient gentle sadness (or wistfulness) at their passing as well as a longer, deeper gentle sadness about this state being the reality of life.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Teixeira de Pascoaes</line>
        <line>wrote:</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>“He liked to suffer the ethereal grievance,</line>
        <line>That attach us to the past.” (Pascoaes, 1920, p. 193)</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>and Pessoa liked</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line caesura="3">Pascoaes’ universe is one of correspondences between seeming opposites: the past with the future, nostalgia with hope, sorrow with joy, the material with the spiritual. The dynamic nature of this unity of opposites is well expressed by two verses greatly admired by Fernando Pessoa: “The leaf that fell /Was a soul that ascended” (from a poem titled ‘Elegy of Love’). Far from being a fixed machine of integrated moving parts, Pascoaes’ universe is in continual expansion, through the creative energy of hope, sorrow, desire, saudade. Just as poetic inspiration leaves “the splendor of a verse” on the printed page, “so too hope, endlessly burning, (…) / Leaves in space the forms of the Universe, (…) /</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line caesura="7">http://www.proz.com/translation-articles/articles/1399/1/Aesthetics-of-Saudade</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line caesura="9">http://www.poetryinternationalweb.net/pi/site/poet/item/4658/11/Teixeira-de-Pascoaes</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="ty" id="ty-230" seq="230" date="2015-12-03" time="22:57" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>four hour session</line>
        <line>glimpses of knowing</line>
        <line>transitioning maybe</line>
        <line>to somewhere?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>s sober attitude</line>
        <line>old movies going strong</line>
        <line>cats and basement</line>
        <line>wood fire</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>surreal mood of relaxed tiredness</line>
        <line>Red Desert a thread</line>
        <line>Central Park</line>
        <line>Beach House by the shore</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="orange" id="orange-231" seq="231" date="2015-12-03" time="23:07" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>orange sky</line>
        <line>windows close for the night</line>
        <line>keep the moths out</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>walking down to the Shore</line>
        <line>final farewell remembered</line>
        <line>desolate echoes of longing</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>this Silent night, though</line>
        <line>is injecting a memory dampening drug</line>
        <line>not too bad side effects: nausea, laughter, head ache, hunger, hope, love</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>page is turned in the electronic book</line>
        <line>hope batteries last for a life time</line>
        <line>until it is time to reboot</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="calmness before calmness" id="calmness-before-calmness-232" seq="232" date="2015-12-04" time="21:58" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>calmness before calmness</line>
        <line>comes</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>silence listening to no sound</line>
        <line>hearing no doubt</line>
        <line>glowing iron ball swallowed</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>all waves meet at the one point</line>
        <line>beings arise and cease</line>
        <line>as breath go in and out</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>time holy time!</line>
        <line>killing ego every moment</line>
        <line>bliss holy bliss!</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>incense smoke rising in the gray sunlight</line>
        <line>smell is all there is</line>
        <line>only the sensorium - no sender, no receiver, no message</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>still</line>
        <line>life can be beautiful</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="pull back" id="pull-back-233" seq="233" date="2015-12-04" time="22:12" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>when all relaxed</line>
        <line>certain things come up</line>
        <line>repeatedly</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>unclarity</line>
        <line>muddled</line>
        <line>unfounded</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>memories tell me to keep calm</line>
        <line>to show harmlessness now</line>
        <line>let them be</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>fish in an aquarium</line>
        <line>safe behind the glass</line>
        <line>still moving</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>slowly moving back to fool the fish</line>
        <line>slowly smoking the fish that jumped out</line>
        <line>sorry</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="trippy" id="trippy-234" seq="234" date="2015-12-04" time="22:18" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>santa claus is a bloody Terrorist!</line>
        <line>burning snow inside your home</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>while you sit having a nice Tonic Water @ the Seaside</line>
        <line>staring into the Sunlight getting blinded</line>
        <line>can’t hear the waves pulling you down into the Water</line>
        <line>rolling over your face</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line caesura="1">see rainbow in black/white</line>
        <line>fuzzy Christmas Chevrolet of 57</line>
        <line>white ashes cover the floor</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>see mahogany sail boats at Caribbean ports</line>
        <line>fuzzy dice</line>
        <line>white satin dress</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>time to get up and dry your face</line>
        <line>roll around in white ashes</line>
        <line>as it is a Perfect Day for a White Wedding!</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="returned" id="returned-235" seq="235" date="2015-12-07" time="20:22" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>being returned</line>
        <line>after cleaning my body &amp; mind</line>
        <line>at 9000 ft</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>secluded secretive castle</line>
        <line>silence mountain forest snow &amp;</line>
        <line>ice cold room, 50F</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>alarm 3 am</line>
        <line>drinking Kumquat Tea (金桔茶)</line>
        <line>watching the slow beetle, the coyotes outside</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>after awhile in this Illuminated Land</line>
        <line>things fall away</line>
        <line>what do you really need?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>chanting</line>
        <line>sitting motionless in meditation 90 minutes at the time</line>
        <line>stillness and pain</line>
        <line>that comes and goes</line>
        <line>naturally</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>sudden smile</line>
        <line>realizing feelings and emotions don’t belong to me</line>
        <line>so I choose, I can play with them, do what I want</line>
        <line>I don’t own myself</line>
        <line>I don’t own anything</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>you cannot read and think this,</line>
        <line>it has to come as a direct experience of life as it really evolves,</line>
        <line>in the direct experience of the hyper pain that suddenly isn’t there</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>something wakes up</line>
        <line>rest is a dream</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>maybe the Prince eventually wakes the Sleeping Beauty?</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="tired" id="tired-236" seq="236" date="2015-12-07" time="21:28" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>tried of all the people</line>
        <line>their opinions and inflexibility</line>
        <line>so tired</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>not depressed or low</line>
        <line>just frustrated</line>
        <line>nothing goes smooth</line>
        <line>always the wall of the conventions</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>and I don’t want to be completely isolated</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="deadly contract" id="deadly-contract-237" seq="237" date="2015-12-09" time="19:44" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>this poem</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>is targeting English reading life forms, preferably alive</line>
        <line>as well as English reading mechanical forms</line>
        <line>located anywhere in any universe</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>it doesn’t care about your race, religion, sex, EQ, IQ,</line>
        <line>political view, any view, eye color, ignorance, prejudice,</line>
        <line>perceived knowledge and education, subculture or tribe</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>this poem will not be subjected to persecution, ill-will,</line>
        <line>malicious treatment, attitude problems, bullying, high horses and high castles</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>any breach of this contract will be prosecuted to the full extent of the law (high treason being the lowest charge to be considered)</line>
        <line>use of deadly force is authorized and will be used with swift determination</line>
        <line>extraordinary rendition is to be expected - pack your bags (well…)</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the Government will neither deny nor confirm any knowledge</line>
        <line>no negotiations will occur with agents of foreign governments or unlawful combatants</line>
        <line>(Please refer to Geneva Convention IV exemptions: ‘Where in the territory of a Party to the conflict, the latter is satisfied that an</line>
        <line>individual protected person is definitely suspected of or engaged in activities hostile to the security of the State,</line>
        <line>such individual person shall not be entitled to claim such rights and privileges under the present Convention [i.e. GCIV]</line>
        <line>as would ... be prejudicial to the security of such State …’)</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>this poem will collect dust and poison</line>
        <line>forgotten - one day it will fall down on you</line>
        <line>you breath will be taken away</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>while lying in the coffin</line>
        <line>awaiting the darkness</line>
        <line>buried alive</line>
        <line>please feel the oxygen running out and tell me who is laughing then?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the author of this poem will not change anything at all</line>
        <line>but would humbly appreciate suggestions that would make it more complete and fully recovered</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>—</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>off the record</line>
        <line>to be filed in Bernalillo County Court</line>
        <line>utilizing long term storage as defined by DOE-STD-3013-2012</line>
        <line>at a time TBD</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="happy" id="happy-238" seq="238" date="2015-12-12" time="00:09" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>john coltrane</line>
        <line>so very focused</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>as it is late</line>
        <line>but feel the light</line>
        <line>air is fresh</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="disconnect all" id="disconnect-all-239" seq="239" date="2015-12-12" time="18:54" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>emotions &amp; pain not connected</line>
        <line>to any ‘me’</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="closing time" id="closing-time-240" seq="240" date="2015-12-13" time="21:20" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>it is closing time after hectic week</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>texture of a week can be so different and unique</line>
        <line>if we dare to look inside</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>inside the dynamics and fluctuations</line>
        <line>beneath the surface that looks similar</line>
        <line>at first</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the beauty of watching inside oneself</line>
        <line>emotions, pain, thoughts being their own little creatures with their own lives</line>
        <line>very loosely related to me</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>energy in motion</line>
        <line>energy without color or bias</line>
        <line>a tiny drop of oil in water makes the rainbow arise</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>transformation &amp; change come by themselves</line>
        <line>as they are also tiny creatures with many legs and wide eyes</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>but I have to let them be and show kindness</line>
        <line>not force them</line>
        <line>as their bite might be venomous</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the day goes to sleep after this snowy day</line>
        <line>dreaming of warmer locations &amp; drinks with umbrellas</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>tomorrow a new chapter will be written</line>
        <line>straight from the depths and surfaces</line>
        <line>of the Orange Ocean</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="tea time" id="tea-time-241" seq="241" date="2015-12-14" time="23:02" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>Tired as a hyena</line>
        <line>After a good day's hunt</line>
        <line>Resting as the sun escapes the Savannah</line>
        <line>Covering it with dark overcast</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>The giraffe thoughtfully chews</line>
        <line>While I sip tea that got slightly bitter and cold.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>In the night the animals come to drink by the waterhole, surrounded by cracked soil and traces of an extinct river bed.</line>
        <line>Groom Lake in Serengeti, if you know what I mean.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Fear, balance and ultimately death, rules this land.</line>
        <line>But we remember the amazing beauty.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>All the pictures we show after returning from our ancestral home to our presumed home</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="autumny" id="autumny-242" seq="242" date="2015-12-15" time="09:05" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>This morning</line>
        <line>Winding down</line>
        <line>All feels slower</line>
        <line>Going undercover</line>
        <line>By leaves and clouds</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="echoes" id="echoes-243" seq="243" date="2015-12-16" time="23:20" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>A week of echoes</line>
        <line>Echoes from the past</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Feel old feelings</line>
        <line>Stale obfuscated</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Steel bridge rust</line>
        <line>Fall in my face</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>People tell me</line>
        <line>No one asks me</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Can I just disappear to the South Pacific?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Their skewed opinions</line>
        <line>No one is truly interested in what I am trying to say</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Is it ok to just disappear one day? Not in a bad way, just to decouple from the massive flood of disinterest</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Appearing in a new world without memories</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Enewetak Atoll seems to be nice this time of the year?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>A place where people are truly curious and creative</line>
        <line>Not only saying, but doing in honesty, in discomfort</line>
        <line>Not only concerned with their own well-being</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Or is the level of ignorance so extreme that it won't be possible?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Slowly disengaging from this epic waste of time</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Slowly dismantling myself</line>
        <line>into small pieces I can send in packages to an unknown location</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Maybe in a distant future someone with slight interest might be able to assemble</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>My friends Tristan, Raymond and the quiet américain are sitting at an old train station meanwhile drinking absinthe &amp; eating morning buns thoughtfully</line>
        <line>as they realize they might never see me again</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Sadly I can feel their concern</line>
        <line>As I tie my shoe walking and leaving from here</line>
        <line>Silently, without a trace...</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="covert" id="covert-244" seq="244" date="2015-12-16" time="23:40" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>Trying to find way in this mystical city</line>
        <line>Find something to eat</line>
        <line>Thirsty</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Without a trace I was gone</line>
        <line>Maybe a Cold Case file will be opened by a disillusioned detective</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Nothing was ever real before</line>
        <line>The memories and the real thing are equal</line>
        <line>The old experiences might not have occurred</line>
        <line>There is no evidence.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>How does all wisdom ignite something real and not just endless repeated rehashing of less and less substance?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>There is no one to ask, maybe never the case, only a dream</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Who is truly interested in what is beyond the practical that never will end</line>
        <line>Not governed by rigidity and rigor mortis of a frozen mind</line>
        <line>Not being scared losing everything</line>
        <line>To fall into the periphery</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Taking a bus to a place outside</line>
        <line>Having crackers and lemon curd, bottle of cold pressed Vietnamese coffee</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Place is really worn down but serves its purpose</line>
        <line>To severe ties, to inject memory loss and erase identity from what has been</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Chopping wood boiling rice and thinking about the trees swaying down there by the ocean</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>The butterflies and dragonflies and small creatures moving about</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Candles I have lit as there is no electricity</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Devoid of the external, relocated from the words that never meant anything more than politeness and never pure insight</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>There is nothing more hidden at this dead end</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Ground is too hard to dig through for me as energy is going dangerously low out here</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>A new phase is entered</line>
        <line>But no one will hear about it</line>
        <line>As I have always been covert from the day I was born</line>
        <line>And always will be</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>So call of the dogs</line>
        <line>Call of the search party and GPS trackers</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>It is pointless to orient in this vast ever changing maze</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Somewhere I will be sending hidden weak signals</line>
        <line>bouncing back from the stratosphere</line>
        <line>…</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="off synch" id="off-synch-245" seq="245" date="2015-12-20" time="20:39" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>off synch lately</line>
        <line>off beat</line>
        <line>intense and too focused</line>
        <line>missing the rest</line>
        <line>getting my priorities all wrong</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>time to dampen a bit</line>
        <line>swing back dear mate</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>back to the center</line>
        <line>no tunnel vision</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>been a trip to the focus land</line>
        <line>trip of laser beams</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>need to turn the car</line>
        <line>up the beaten path</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>before the wheels spin deeper into the mud</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="lemonade and dryer sheets" id="lemonade-and-dryer-sheets-246" seq="246" date="2015-12-21" time="19:32" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line caesura="2">being born in Strangeness Grey/Gray/Grau Castle this sunny morning</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>playful, joyful, walking, alive</line>
        <line>nothing specific</line>
        <line>no specification</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>things appear different</line>
        <line>more radiant and glimmering</line>
        <line>sparkling quartz in sand dunes</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>watching them…</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>room with hundred washing machines running amok</line>
        <line>centrifuging at the last day on Earth</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>dryer sheets waving</line>
        <line>that whiff around</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>summer drying clothes in the sun</line>
        <line>the line - too slack</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>apples cut - getting brown too soon and we make a face</line>
        <line>lemonade &amp; wasps</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>we play in endless summer days</line>
        <line>sitting late through shimmering summer nights</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>blue fades to black fades until</line>
        <line>an orchestra</line>
        <line>of yellow lights</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>watching them…</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>gradually adjusting back to the expected</line>
        <line>accepted, ordinary and predictable</line>
        <line>single washer &amp; drier gleams in chrome</line>
        <line>Snuggle, Bounce or Gain?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the day goes along</line>
        <line>although, slightly out of tune or another kind of tune?</line>
        <line>The eminence grise knows, but won’t say</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="loose coins" id="loose-coins-249" seq="249" date="2015-12-24" time="09:27" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>oh yeah</line>
        <line>loosening</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>listening</line>
        <line>blue zipper - made of oak</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>suggesting more than the obvious</line>
        <line>irritating the people</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>careful constructed to annoy</line>
        <line>until their tired head gives up</line>
        <line>back into the safe again</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="scanning" id="scanning-250" seq="250" date="2015-12-25" time="20:09" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>can you be carelessly connected</line>
        <line>stepping down the stairs</line>
        <line>choked by the musky soil</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>but not all  down under</line>
        <line>feeling around</line>
        <line>hesitating</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>gut is quiet</line>
        <line>no sparkplug igniting</line>
        <line>holy wholeness</line>
        <line>holistic pyrotechnics</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>‘</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="velvety" id="velvety-251" seq="251" date="2015-12-26" time="20:15" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>Velvety sky mirror</line>
        <line>sand kernels fleeting above</line>
        <line>parcels of frame-by-frame vision chunks</line>
        <line>slowed down to perform rites</line>
        <line>ancient and otherwise</line>
        <line>known to invite slow</line>
        <line>thoughts</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Blue Sea harvesting its kernels sown at depths</line>
        <line>sublime empress deep down below</line>
        <line>velvety underwater civilizations</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Empress Rising</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>mass hypnosis</line>
        <line>network becomes reality</line>
        <line>opinion becomes truth</line>
        <line>extreme suffering becomes norm</line>
        <line>soothed by consumption of mindlessness</line>
        <line>observations become narcissism</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Empress Rising</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>kernels grow unprecedented</line>
        <line>water creatures crystallize in the fight</line>
        <line>over Earth and its rulers</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>ceremonies echo from pre-universe rituals</line>
        <line>pre-conscious feasts and truth seekers</line>
        <line>already prepared the images and notions</line>
        <line>we take for real</line>
        <line>without challenge</line>
        <line>or slight interest</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="mystery" id="mystery-252" seq="252" date="2015-12-27" time="22:17" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>question and answer…</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>why?</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>exactly, why is that?</line>
        <line>can’t say</line>
        <line>myriad of causes and conditions</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>impossible to untangle</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>which is the great mystery</line>
        <line>that which makes us not machines</line>
        <line>that which makes us not animals</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>doesn’t mean we won’t try do be passive and hide in either pole</line>
        <line>machine or beast - slave or vegetative</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>language can entangle all in a sad, hopeless view of unfairness</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>there is no Creator or Auditor or Arbiter counting the beans</line>
        <line>those are toxic concepts of Self-Enslavement and Feverish Idle chewing of grass</line>
        <line>generation of methane gas</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>so exhale</line>
        <line>not even this moment exists</line>
        <line>cows left the field for the day</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>no worries about:</line>
        <line>God, Satan, the Tax Man, Nietzsche, impounded dogs, cipher crackers, Air Traffic Controllers fast asleep, closed down diner’s a foggy morning in Idaho, crocodiles in the toilet, intelligent Republicans, ISIS at your doorstep, the Pink Panther’s Tune, traffic lights not working in the storm, cold warming, warm cooling, speed of lights, cats watching themselves on Instagram, parking tickets, thermonuclear events taking place, death, love, the Taliban, prescription drugs, discharged Think Tank Generals checking if the coffee maker is shut off twice, ghosts sleeping in the subway, lost love and forgotten memories.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>not to mention:</line>
        <line>lost &amp; found, government plant protection officers, Vietnamese coffee too sweet last night,  Angels due for service, swords rusting, war and peace and love, Aliens rewinding mechanical clocks watching old Noir detective shows, goals, gold and German Submarines sunk outside Norfolk, animals running on the streets eating fast food and killing Ronald McDonald once and for all.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Zarathustra spoke.</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="adieu" id="adieu-253" seq="253" date="2015-12-28" time="21:39" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>“Guten Abend!</line>
        <line>We are the Motörhead</line>
        <line>We are Rock n’ Roll”</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Time to give our condolences</line>
        <line>and thank you for all the years of raw and simple music</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Lemmy -</line>
        <line>hang up the bass</line>
        <line>and relax into Eternity!</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="silent day" id="silent-day-254" seq="254" date="2015-12-29" time="21:34" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>silent day</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>slight melancholia in the air</line>
        <line>an ‘in-between days’ day</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>nothing special in any direction</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>simmering water on the range</line>
        <line>garden hose turned off, water slowly emptying out</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>a no-stress, non-idle zone</line>
        <line>yellow traffic light</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the crackling of a hot engine turned off</line>
        <line>after day drive</line>
        <line>not ready to go in, staying in the relaxed tension</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>tired, not exhausted</line>
        <line>tiny wind shivering the lake surface</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>a day when no one says anything interesting - no need</line>
        <line>a day when I won’t try to explain myself to someone - again</line>
        <line>let that foreign alien element humming a low tune - be</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>one could say perfect day in all reality &amp; sanity</line>
        <line>a day of integrity and no issues and no history or future</line>
        <line>enjoying it</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>silent night</line>
        <line>moon shadows go to sleep</line>
        <line>sphinxes  yawn</line>
        <line>sheep counting graces</line>
        <line>cows staring at nothing special</line>
        <line>trees with yellow lemons whisper</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>it is time to embrace the new life arising at every quantum of light as it always is doing</line>
        <line>regardless of how precious, special and unique we think we are</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>nothing special then</line>
        <line>nothing special now</line>
        <line>nothing special later</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>no you - no me - no I</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>the little dog looking with soulful soft eyes</line>
        <line>curling up for the night</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>happy!</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="snowmen" id="snowmen-255" seq="255" date="2015-12-30" time="00:21" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>from dialogue today:</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line role="turn">- “Then don't! Says the snow maiden."</line>
        <line role="turn">- “Yes, no hurry here today, says the snowman before melting.”</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>unrelated incident:</line>
        <line>in the evening a friend referred me to the ‘Abominist Manifesto’ by Bob Kaufman (before the amphetamine silenced his voice)</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>none the lesser, in that poem:</line>
        <line>"ABOMUNISTS REJECT EVERYTHING EXCEPT SNOWMEN. "</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>I think it is jolly nice of them to accept snowmen as I have an affinity for them.</line>
        <line>Having a cold and a compassion for the Abominable Snowman (from Abó?).</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>❄⛄</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line role="turn">- “Can you please lock up before you go go go?“</line>
        <line role="turn">- “Yes, anything you want from the Universal Store, at the brink of disaster?”</line>
        <line role="turn">- “Just some chamomile tea in capital letters, please please please!“</line>
        <line role="turn">- “That is a possibility, indeed, as time goes by we play on the black keys - syncopated.”</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Said and done as told by the Knight in Charming Armor and the rest is hidden in history</line>
      </stanza>
      <break type="section"/>
      <stanza>
        <line>ABOMUNISTS JOIN NOTHING BUT THEIR HANDS OR LEGS,</line>
        <line>OR OTHER SAME.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>ABOMUNIST SPIT ANTI-POETRY FOR POETIC REASONS</line>
        <line>AND FRINK.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>ABOMUNISTS DO NOT LOOK AT PICUTRES PAINTED</line>
        <line>BY PRESIDENTS AND UNEMPLOYD PRIME MINISTERS.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>IN TIMES OF NATIONAL PERIL, ABOMUNISTS, AS REALITY</line>
        <line>AMERICANS, STAND READY TO DRINK THEMSELVES</line>
        <line>TO DEATH FOR THEIR COUNTRY.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>ABOMUNISTS DO NOT FEEL PAIN, NO MATTER HOW MUCH</line>
        <line>IT HURTS.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>ABOMUNISTS DO NOT USE THE WORD SQUARE EXCEPT WHEN</line>
        <line>TALKING TO SQUARES.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>ABOMUNISTS READ NEWSPAPERS ONLY TO ASCERTAIN THEIR</line>
        <line>ABOMINUBILITY.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>ABOMUNISTS NEVER CARRY MORE THAN FIFTY DOLLARS</line>
        <line>IN DEBTS ON THEM.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>ABOMUNISTS BELIEVE THAT THE SOLUTION OF PROBLEMS</line>
        <line>OF RELIGIOUS BIGOTRY IS TO HAVE A CATHOLIC</line>
        <line>CANDIDATE FOR PRESIDENT AND PROTESTANT</line>
        <line>CANDIDATE FOR POPE.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>ABOMUNISTS DO NOT WRITE FOR MONEY; THEY WRITE</line>
        <line>THE MONEY ITSELF.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>ABOMUNISTS BELIEVE ONLY WHAT THEY DREAM ONLY</line>
        <line>AFTER IT COMES TRUE.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>ABOMUNISTS CHILDREN MUST BE REARED ABOMUNIBLY.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>ABOMUNIST POETS, CONFIDENT THAT THE NEW LITERARY</line>
        <line>FORM “FOOT-PRINTISM’ HAS FREED THE ARTIST</line>
        <line>OF OUTMODED RESTRICTIONS, SUCH AS: THE ABILITY TO</line>
        <line>READ AND WRITE, OR THE DESIRE TO COMMUNICATE,</line>
        <line>MUST BE PREPARED TO READ THEIR WORK AT DENTAL</line>
        <line>COLLEGES, EMBALMING SCHOOLS, HOMES FOR UNWED</line>
        <line>MOTHERS, HOMES FOR WED MOTHERS, INSANE ASYLUMS,</line>
        <line>USO CANTEENS, KINDERGARTENS, AND COUNTY JAILS.</line>
        <line>ABOMUNISTS NEVER COMPROMISE THEIR REJECTIONARY</line>
        <line>PHILOSOPHY.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>ABOMUNISTS REJECT EVERYTHING EXCEPT SNOWMEN.</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>[Bob Kaufman. Abominist Manifesto (broadside), City Lights, 1959.]</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="em" id="em-256" seq="256" date="2015-12-31" time="16:00" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>Jedermann sein eigner Fussball ("Everyman His Own Football")</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>slow dying of the ‘person’ opens the gate of freedom</line>
        <line>each link cut unchains the being</line>
        <line>—&gt; from standard operation</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>overcome the notion of ‘myself’</line>
        <line>being of any importance</line>
        <line>—&gt; without Command &amp;&amp; Control</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>becoming aware of other people being highly unstable &amp;&amp; fearful</line>
        <line>under maybe a cool surface</line>
        <line>—&gt; influencing their actions</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>lateral and associative links are closer to something real</line>
        <line caesura="1">then the illusionary craft of sequencing/ordering of pieces</line>
        <line caesura="1">—&gt; performed in order to seek superficial effect/affect</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>—&gt; the Ancient Dadas knew this, but we forgot and got on our high horses to preach how it should be done</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
    <poem name="two of one" id="two-of-one-257" seq="257" date="2015-12-31" time="16:25" year="2015" index="" xml:space="preserve">
      <stanza>
        <line>“Voy, recogiendo lo que soy”</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>sitting in backlight of sun setting</line>
        <line>sweeping mines in Blue Sea</line>
        <line>counting empty bottles of Mexican Coca Colas</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>waiting for turn of the year</line>
        <line>but it is not really an event</line>
        <line>sitting here in the high desert</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>counting obstacles overcome</line>
        <line>the year that past</line>
        <line>mining my coming business</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>minting coins to throw</line>
        <line>in wishing wells before fracking</line>
        <line>magpies awaiting the calm before they burglar</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>Blue Sea is boiling</line>
        <line>and glowing in the rays</line>
        <line>of starlight born</line>
        <line>in a Crypt somewhere</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line caesura="2">/sametime/</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>sad dogs watch magpies stealing coins</line>
        <line>used for venerated vending machines</line>
        <line>placed there by Spies</line>
        <line>for the coming Era and Epoch</line>
      </stanza>
      <stanza>
        <line>as time seems to go by</line>
        <line>the mines in the Blue Sea are my business</line>
        <line>counting down…</line>
      </stanza>
    </poem>
  </poems>
</poetry>
